(47, 2, 4, 'And learned Thy love''s deep woe -'),
(47, 3, 1, 'Thy glory, Lord: this living waste'),
(47, 3, 2, 'To us no rest can give;'),
(47, 3, 3, 'Our path is on with earnest haste,'),
(47, 3, 4, 'Lord, in Thy rest to live.'),
(47, 4, 1, 'Our happiness, O Lord, with Thee'),
(47, 4, 2, 'Is long laid up in store,'),
(47, 4, 3, 'For that blest day when Thee we''ll see,'),
(47, 4, 4, 'And conflict will be o''er.'),
(47, 5, 1, 'Yes, love divine in Thee we know;'),
(47, 5, 2, 'The Father''s glories soon'),
(47, 5, 3, 'Shall burst upon our ravished view,'),
(47, 5, 4, 'Thyself our joy and crown.'),
(47, 6, 1, 'Soon shall we see Thee as Thou art,'),
(47, 6, 2, 'O hope for ever blest!'),
(47, 6, 3, 'Thou''lt call us, in our heav''nly part,'),
(47, 6, 4, 'The Father''s house, to rest.'),
(47, 7, 1, 'O rest ineffable, divine,'),
(47, 7, 2, 'the rest of God above,'),
(47, 7, 3, 'Where we shall ever see Thee shine,'),
(47, 7, 4, 'Our joy, eternal love!'),
(48, 1, 1, 'O how inscrutable,'),
(48, 1, 2, 'Yea, how unsearchable'),
(48, 1, 3, 'Art Thou, O God!'),
(48, 1, 4, 'Now lowly bowing,'),
(48, 1, 5, 'Thy greatness owning,'),
(48, 1, 6, 'We praise and laud.'),
(48, 2, 1, 'Thy Son beloved'),
(48, 2, 2, 'Knew in its fulness'),
(48, 2, 3, 'That heart of Thine.'),
(48, 2, 4, 'He has declared Thee'),
(48, 2, 5, 'And here revealed Thee'),
(48, 2, 6, 'In love divine.'),
(48, 3, 1, 'In adoration,'),
(48, 3, 2, 'Deep contemplation,'),
(48, 3, 3, 'We worship Thee;'),
(48, 3, 4, 'In Christ before Thee'),
(48, 3, 5, 'We shall adore Thee'),
(48, 3, 6, 'Eternally!'),
(49, 1, 1, 'Blest Father of glory, we worship,'),
(49, 1, 2, 'Thy greatness surpasses our praise;'),
(49, 1, 3, 'We bless Thee, Thy Spirit within us'),
(49, 1, 4, 'Gives power to these heavenly lays.'),
(49, 2, 1, 'We think of the Man in Thy presence,'),
(49, 2, 2, 'Set down there, exalted as head;'),
(49, 2, 3, 'Once raised by the might of Thy power,'),
(49, 2, 4, 'When numbered along with the dead.'),
(49, 3, 1, 'We think of the glory that chose us,'),
(49, 3, 2, '''Twas Thine, blessed Father, the Source;'),
(49, 3, 3, 'The glory of love that redeemed us,'),
(49, 3, 4, 'Through Jesus, the Man of Thy choice.'),
(49, 4, 1, 'As marked out beforehand for sonship,'),
(49, 4, 2, 'We praise now the glory of grace'),
(49, 4, 3, 'And bow in Thy presence and worship,'),
(49, 4, 4, 'As conscious, in Christ, of our place.'),
(50, 1, 1, 'Lord, in Thee we taste the sweetness'),
(50, 1, 2, 'Of the Tree of Life above;'),
(50, 1, 3, 'Taste its own eternal meetness'),
(50, 1, 4, 'For the heav''nly land we love.'),
(50, 2, 1, 'In eternal counsels purposed,'),
(50, 2, 2, 'Food of heav''nly life to be;'),
(50, 2, 3, 'Fresh and ever new are yielded'),
(50, 2, 4, 'Fruits of life on that blest Tree.'),
(50, 3, 1, 'Varied fruits of richest flavour'),
(50, 3, 2, 'Offers still the Tree divine;'),
(50, 3, 3, 'One itself, the same for ever,'),
(50, 3, 4, 'Every precious fruit is Thine;'),
(50, 4, 1, 'Fruits that now our souls have tasted'),
(50, 4, 2, 'By the Spirit from above,'),
(50, 4, 3, 'While through desert lands we''ve hasted;'),
(50, 4, 4, 'Fruits of perfect, endless love.'),
(51, 1, 1, 'O Lord, Thy love''s unbounded,'),
(51, 1, 2, 'So sweet, so full, so free;'),
(51, 1, 3, 'My soul is all transported'),
(51, 1, 4, 'Whene''er I think of Thee!'),
(51, 2, 1, 'Yet, Lord, alas! what weakness'),
(51, 2, 2, 'Within myself I find;'),
(51, 2, 3, 'No infant''s changing pleasure'),
(51, 2, 4, 'Is like my wand''ring mind.'),
(51, 3, 1, 'And yet Thy love''s unchanging,'),
(51, 3, 2, 'And doth recall my heart'),
(51, 3, 3, 'To joy in all its brightness,'),
(51, 3, 4, 'The peace its beams impart.'),
(51, 4, 1, 'Yet sure, if in Thy presence'),
(51, 4, 2, 'My soul still constant were,'),
(51, 4, 3, 'Mine eye would, more familiar,'),
(51, 4, 4, 'Its brighter glories bear.'),
(51, 5, 1, 'And thus Thy deep perfections'),
(51, 5, 2, 'Much better should I know,'),
(51, 5, 3, 'And with adoring fervour'),
(51, 5, 4, 'In this Thy nature grow.'),
(51, 6, 1, 'Still sweet ''tis to discover,'),
(51, 6, 2, 'If clouds have dimmed my sight,'),
(51, 6, 3, 'When passed, eternal Lover,'),
(51, 6, 4, 'Towards me, as e''er, Thou''rt bright.'),
(51, 7, 1, 'O keep my soul, then, Jesus,'),
(51, 7, 2, 'Abiding still with Thee,'),
(51, 7, 3, 'And, if I wander, teach me'),
(51, 7, 4, 'Soon back to Thee to flee;'),
(51, 8, 1, 'That all Thy gracious favour'),
(51, 8, 2, 'May to my soul be known;'),
(51, 8, 3, 'And, versed in this Thy goodness,'),
(51, 8, 4, 'My hopes Thyself shalt crown.'),
(52, 1, 1, 'We sing to Thee, blest Father,'),
(52, 1, 2, 'As moved by light divine'),
(52, 1, 3, 'In realms of wondrous counsel,'),
(52, 1, 4, 'Where Jesus'' glories shine.'),
(52, 1, 5, 'We praise with hearts adoring,'),
(52, 1, 6, 'In heav''nly places blest;'),
(52, 1, 7, 'Fruit of eternal purpose,'),
(52, 1, 8, 'Where now in joy we rest.'),
(52, 2, 1, 'We praise Thee, glorious Father,'),
(52, 2, 2, 'As objects of Thy grace,'),
(52, 2, 3, 'Who for Thine own heart''s pleasure'),
(52, 2, 4, 'Are now before Thy face:'),
(52, 2, 5, 'Thy sons marked out for glory -'),
(52, 2, 6, 'Known from eternity -'),
(52, 2, 7, 'With Christ Thy Well-beloved,'),
(52, 2, 8, 'Object supreme to Thee.'),
(52, 3, 1, 'Who else but Thee, O Father,'),
(52, 3, 2, 'Could in Thine only Son'),
(52, 3, 3, 'So bless us with Thy Spirit,'),
(52, 3, 4, 'And have us for Thine own?'),
(52, 3, 5, 'Soon shall we be for ever'),
(52, 3, 6, 'With Christ in glory; then'),
(52, 3, 7, 'We''ll shine in His blest image'),
(52, 3, 8, 'Eternally, Amen!'),
(53, 1, 1, 'We''ll sing of God''s wonderful gospel,'),
(53, 1, 2, 'Glad tidings concerning His Son!'),
(53, 1, 3, 'Christ''s Person, His work, and His glory,'),
(53, 1, 4, 'We love Him for all He has done.'),
(53, 2, 1, 'Equality His in the Godhead,'),
(53, 2, 2, 'His Person is ever the Same;'),
(53, 2, 3, 'But stooping in grace into manhood'),
(53, 2, 4, 'To save us, lost sinners, He came.'),
(53, 3, 1, 'His work, praise His Name! He completed'),
(53, 3, 2, 'Alone, when He died on the tree;'),
(53, 3, 3, 'The judgment of sin was His burden,'),
(53, 3, 4, 'He bore it for you and for me.'),
(53, 4, 1, 'Triumphant His present position,'),
(53, 4, 2, 'Ascended at God''s own right hand,'),
(53, 4, 3, 'Attesting God''s full satisfaction;'),
(53, 4, 4, 'Accepted in Him now we stand.'),
(53, 5, 1, 'The Father''s delight is in Jesus,'),
(53, 5, 2, 'And those whom His blood has secured,'),
(53, 5, 3, 'The Spirit would keep Him before us,'),
(53, 5, 4, 'Our living and glorious Lord.'),
(53, 6, 1, 'Through Christ we have present salvation,'),
(53, 6, 2, 'From sin and the world would we turn,'),
(53, 6, 3, 'And walk here in true separation,'),
(53, 6, 4, 'Awaiting our Lord''s near return.'),
(54, 1, 1, 'How sweet the name of Jesus sounds'),
(54, 1, 2, 'In a believer''s ear!'),
(54, 1, 3, 'It soothes his sorrows, heals his wounds,'),
(54, 1, 4, 'And drives away His fear.'),
(54, 2, 1, 'It makes the wounded spirit whole,'),
(54, 2, 2, 'It calms the troubled breast;'),
(54, 2, 3, '''Tis manna to the hungry soul,'),
(54, 2, 4, 'And to the weary rest.'),
(54, 3, 1, 'Blest Name! the rock on which we build,'),
(54, 3, 2, 'Our shield and hiding place;'),
(54, 3, 3, 'Our never-failing treasury, filled'),
(54, 3, 4, 'With boundless stores of grace.'),
(54, 4, 1, 'Jesus! our Saviour, Shepherd, Friend,'),
(54, 4, 2, 'Thou Prophet, Priest, and King,'),
(54, 4, 3, 'Our Lord, our Life, our Way, our End,'),
(54, 4, 4, 'Accept the praise we bring.'),
(54, 5, 1, 'Weak is the effort of our heart,'),
(54, 5, 2, 'And cold our warmest thought;'),
(54, 5, 3, 'But when we see Thee as Thou art,'),
(54, 5, 4, 'We''ll praise Thee as we ought.'),
(54, 6, 1, 'Till then we would Thy love proclaim'),
(54, 6, 2, 'With every fleeting breath;'),
(54, 6, 3, 'And triumph in Thy blessed Name'),
(54, 6, 4, 'Which quells the power of death.'),
(55, 1, 1, 'Through waves, through clouds and storms,'),
(55, 1, 2, 'God gently clears the way;'),
(55, 1, 3, 'We wait His time; so shall the night'),
(55, 1, 4, 'Soon end in blissful day.'),
(55, 2, 1, 'He everywhere hath sway,'),
(55, 2, 2, 'And all things serve His might;'),
(55, 2, 3, 'His every act pure blessing is,'),
(55, 2, 4, 'His path unsullied light.'),
(55, 3, 1, 'When He makes bare His arm,'),
(55, 3, 2, 'Who shall His work withstand?'),
(55, 3, 3, 'When He His people''s cause defends,'),
(55, 3, 4, 'Who then shall stay His hand?'),
(55, 4, 1, 'We leave it to Himself'),
(55, 4, 2, 'To choose and to command;'),
(55, 4, 3, 'With wonder filled, we soon shall see'),
(55, 4, 4, 'How wise, how strong His hand!'),
(55, 5, 1, 'We comprehend Him not,'),
(55, 5, 2, 'Yet earth and heaven tell,'),
(55, 5, 3, 'God sits as sovereign on the throne,'),
(55, 5, 4, 'And ruleth all things well.'),
(56, 1, 1, 'O Lord, how blest our journey,'),
(56, 1, 2, 'Though here on earth we roam,'),
(56, 1, 3, 'Who in the Father''s favour'),
(56, 1, 4, 'Now find our spirits'' home:'),
(56, 1, 5, 'For where Thou now art sitting'),
(56, 1, 6, 'By faith we''ve found repose,'),
(56, 1, 7, 'Free to look up to heaven,'),
(56, 1, 8, 'Since our blest Head arose.'),
(56, 2, 1, 'In spirit there already,'),
(56, 2, 2, 'Soon we ourselves shall be'),
(56, 2, 3, 'In soul and body perfect,'),
(56, 2, 4, 'All glorified, with Thee.'),
(56, 2, 5, 'Thy Father''s love sustains us'),
(56, 2, 6, 'Along the pilgrim way;'),
(56, 2, 7, 'Thy Father''s house, the dwelling'),
(56, 2, 8, 'Made ready for that day.'),
(56, 3, 1, 'The Comforter, now present,'),
(56, 3, 2, 'Assures us of Thy love;'),
(56, 3, 3, 'He is the blessed Earnest'),
(56, 3, 4, 'Of glory there above;'),
(56, 3, 5, 'The river of God''s pleasure'),
(56, 3, 6, 'Is what sustains us now,'),
(56, 3, 7, 'Till Thy new Name''s imprinted'),
(56, 3, 8, 'On every sinless brow.'),
(56, 4, 1, 'Lord, we await Thy glory;'),
(56, 4, 2, 'We have no home but there,'),
(56, 4, 3, 'Where all Thine own together'),
(56, 4, 4, 'Thy joy with Thee shall share.'),
(56, 4, 5, 'No place can fully please us'),
(56, 4, 6, 'Where Thou, O Lord, art not;'),
(56, 4, 7, 'In Thee, and with Thee, ever'),
(56, 4, 8, 'Is found, by grace, our lot.'),
(57, 1, 1, 'Where glory lights the courts on high,'),
(57, 1, 2, 'With highest glory crowned,'),
(57, 1, 3, 'Thee, Lord of power and majesty,'),
(57, 1, 4, 'Celestial hosts surround.'),
(57, 2, 1, 'O who shall sing that path of worth,'),
(57, 2, 2, 'That led up to the throne?'),
(57, 2, 3, 'The Corn of Wheat upon this earth'),
(57, 2, 4, 'Could but abide alone;'),
(57, 3, 1, 'But Thou art risen from the dead,'),
(57, 3, 2, 'And we, as one with Thee,'),
(57, 3, 3, 'Now sing Thy Name, our Lord, our Head,'),
(57, 3, 4, 'A heav''nly company.'),
(57, 4, 1, 'Lord Jesus, Thou art waiting yet'),
(57, 4, 2, 'Till, perfect at Thy side,'),
(57, 4, 3, 'Thy blest companion shall be set,'),
(57, 4, 4, 'Thy fair and spotless bride.'),
(58, 1, 1, 'Lord, we are Thine, bought by Thy blood,'),
(58, 1, 2, 'Once the poor guilty slaves of sin;'),
(58, 1, 3, 'But Thou redeemedst us to God,'),
(58, 1, 4, 'And mad''st Thy Spirit dwell within.'),
(58, 2, 1, 'Lord, we are Thine, Thy claims we own;'),
(58, 2, 2, 'Ourselves to Thee we''d wholly give;'),
(58, 2, 3, 'O may our hearts Thyself enthrone,'),
(58, 2, 4, 'And let us to Thy glory live!'),
(58, 3, 1, 'Here let us each Thy mind display,'),
(58, 3, 2, 'In all Thy gracious image shine;'),
(58, 3, 3, 'And haste that long expected day'),
(58, 3, 4, 'When Thou shalt own that we are Thine.'),
(59, 1, 1, 'The heart of God is love;'),
(59, 1, 2, 'That love extends to Thee,'),
(59, 1, 3, 'For Jesus, His own Son, has died'),
(59, 1, 4, 'To set Thee free.'),
(59, 2, 1, 'Thy God is not far off;'),
(59, 2, 2, 'E''en now in graciousness'),
(59, 2, 3, 'Thou''lt find Him waiting at Thy side,'),
(59, 2, 4, 'Thy soul to bless.'),
(59, 3, 1, 'Jesus, the Lord, has died -'),
(59, 3, 2, 'Has judgment borne for sin;'),
(59, 3, 3, 'Nothing remains to hinder now'),
(59, 3, 4, 'Thine ent''ring in.'),
(59, 4, 1, 'The Holy Spirit giv''n'),
(59, 4, 2, 'Can fill thy heart indeed;'),
(59, 4, 3, 'Blest source within of living grace'),
(59, 4, 4, 'For all Thy need.'),
(59, 5, 1, 'Canst thou remain away'),
(59, 5, 2, 'From such a scene of bliss,'),
(59, 5, 3, 'And God the father''s changeless love'),
(59, 5, 4, 'For ever miss?'),
(59, 6, 1, 'The favour of God''s house'),
(59, 6, 2, 'Stands open now to Thee,'),
(59, 6, 3, 'The Father''s tender love to know'),
(59, 6, 4, 'Eternally!'),
(60, 1, 1, 'Our Father, we praise Thee,'),
(60, 1, 2, 'Thou source of all blessing;'),
(60, 1, 3, 'The Son has revealed Thee'),
(60, 1, 4, 'In fulness of light.'),
(60, 1, 5, 'We joy in Thy presence,'),
(60, 1, 6, 'We worship before Thee'),
(60, 1, 7, 'In love and, all blameless,'),
(60, 1, 8, 'In holiness bright.'),
(61, 1, 1, 'O God, the great "I AM," we worship Thee'),
(61, 1, 2, 'For Thine amazing gift has set men free!'),
(61, 1, 3, 'Redemption''s work has lifted every load,'),
(61, 1, 4, 'Secured a princely people for their God.'),
(61, 2, 1, 'We trace Thy counsels deep ere worlds began,'),
(61, 2, 2, 'And see Thine own great thoughts in making man.'),
(61, 2, 3, 'Thy sovereign will has wrought to set all free,'),
(61, 2, 4, 'To bring in life and joy and liberty.'),
(61, 3, 1, 'No tear-filled eyes then left to chill the joy'),
(61, 3, 2, 'Of new creation''s bliss without alloy!'),
(61, 3, 3, 'All grief by Thy blest service there removed;'),
(61, 3, 4, 'O God of love, Thy love so fully proved!'),
(61, 4, 1, 'How choice the notes that rise responsively,'),
(61, 4, 2, 'In Thine abode throughout eternity!'),
(61, 4, 3, 'The vast extent of the created sphere'),
(61, 4, 4, 'Rejoices, knowing Thou, O God, art near.'),
(62, 1, 1, 'God of the universe,'),
(62, 1, 2, 'What hast Thou wrought!'),
(62, 1, 3, 'Sphere full of love and praise'),
(62, 1, 4, 'Passing all thought!'),
(62, 1, 5, 'While endless days endure,'),
(62, 1, 6, 'Christ and the church secure'),
(62, 1, 7, 'Answer to purpose sure -'),
(62, 1, 8, 'What Thou hast sought!'),
(62, 2, 1, 'We praise and worship Thee'),
(62, 2, 2, 'For what Thou art,'),
(62, 2, 3, 'Thy love and blessedness'),
(62, 2, 4, 'Filling each heart.'),
(62, 2, 5, 'Thus, blessed God, to Thee'),
(62, 2, 6, 'In the assembly be'),
(62, 2, 7, 'Glory eternally -'),
(62, 2, 8, 'Thine own blest part.'),
(63, 1, 1, 'Our God and Father, Thee we bless,'),
(63, 1, 2, 'Extol Thy Name, with joy express'),
(63, 1, 3, 'Praise that is due to Thee.'),
(63, 1, 4, '"Greater then all" we know Thy place,'),
(63, 1, 5, 'But this relationship of grace'),
(63, 1, 6, 'Sets all our spirits free.'),
(63, 2, 1, 'A Father''s love holds all in rest,'),
(63, 2, 2, 'In Christ in heav''nly places blest,'),
(63, 2, 3, 'The Father''s chosen ones.'),
(63, 2, 4, 'O Father, how our hearts expand'),
(63, 2, 5, 'T''wards Thee, as now in Him we stand,'),
(63, 2, 6, 'Accepted as Thy sons!'),
(64, 1, 1, 'O bright and blessed scenes,');
INSERT INTO `hymn_line` (`hymn_no`, `vers_no`, `line_no`, `line_text`) VALUES (64, 1, 2, 'Where sin can never come;'),
(64, 1, 3, 'Whose sight our longing spirit weans'),
(64, 1, 4, 'From earth, where yet we roam.'),
(64, 2, 1, 'And can we call our home'),
(64, 2, 2, 'Our Father''s house on high,'),
(64, 2, 3, 'The rest of God our rest to come'),
(64, 2, 4, 'Our place of liberty?'),
(64, 3, 1, 'Yes! in that light unstained'),
(64, 3, 2, 'Our stainless souls shall live;'),
(64, 3, 3, 'Our hearts'' deep longings more than gained'),
(64, 3, 4, 'When God His rest shall give.'),
(64, 4, 1, 'His presence there, my soul'),
(64, 4, 2, 'Its rest, its joy untold'),
(64, 4, 3, 'Shall find, when endless ages roll,'),
(64, 4, 4, 'And time shall ne''er grow old.'),
(64, 5, 1, 'Like Jesus in that place'),
(64, 5, 2, 'Of light and love supreme,'),
(64, 5, 3, 'Once Man of sorrows, full of grace,'),
(64, 5, 4, 'Heav''n''s blest and endless theme.'),
(64, 6, 1, 'O love supreme and bright,'),
(64, 6, 2, 'Good to the feeblest heart,'),
(64, 6, 3, 'That gives us now as heav''nly light'),
(64, 6, 4, 'What soon shall be our part!'),
(65, 1, 1, 'Lord, as now Thy people gather,'),
(65, 1, 2, 'We delight in Thee as Head,'),
(65, 1, 3, 'Thou dost cherish Thine assembly,'),
(65, 1, 4, 'Glorious Firstborn from the dead.'),
(65, 2, 1, 'In the world Thou art rejected,'),
(65, 2, 2, 'Thine authority disowned.'),
(65, 2, 3, 'Here we seek to guard Thine interests,'),
(65, 2, 4, 'Thou art in our hearts enthroned.'),
(65, 3, 1, 'Help us as we now consider'),
(65, 3, 2, 'How to care for what is Thine.'),
(65, 3, 3, 'May we move as faithful bondmen,'),
(65, 3, 4, 'Subject to Thy will divine!'),
(65, 4, 1, 'Boldness we would seek for meeting'),
(65, 4, 2, 'That which Satan may contrive;'),
(65, 4, 3, 'All we need in skill and wisdom'),
(65, 4, 4, 'We would now from Thee derive.'),
(65, 5, 1, 'Thou dost trust in Thine assembly'),
(65, 5, 2, 'To be faithful to Thy Name,'),
(65, 5, 3, 'As a pure and shining witness,'),
(65, 5, 4, 'Wholly sep''rate, without blame.'),
(65, 6, 1, 'Soon the trump will sound from heaven'),
(65, 6, 2, 'Calling us from earth away,'),
(65, 6, 3, 'Then the vessel Thou hast purchased'),
(65, 6, 4, 'Will be ready for display.'),
(66, 1, 1, 'O gracious God, Thy pleasure'),
(66, 1, 2, 'Is in Thy Christ made known,'),
(66, 1, 3, 'And tells the boundless measure'),
(66, 1, 4, 'Of blessing for Thine own.'),
(66, 1, 5, 'He has Thy presence entered,'),
(66, 1, 6, 'As Man in heav''n is known;'),
(66, 1, 7, 'In Him Thy glory''s centred,'),
(66, 1, 8, 'In Him Thy purpose shown.'),
(66, 2, 1, 'And O what love is beaming'),
(66, 2, 2, 'Refulgent in that face!'),
(66, 2, 3, 'What blessed light is streaming'),
(66, 2, 4, 'From that most glorious place!'),
(66, 2, 5, 'Both love and light proclaiming'),
(66, 2, 6, 'What Thou, the Father, art,'),
(66, 2, 7, 'And wondrous grace revealing,'),
(66, 2, 8, 'With Thine own Son, our part.'),
(66, 3, 1, 'Thou source of every blessing!'),
(66, 3, 2, 'Thou spring of all delight!'),
(66, 3, 3, 'Thy Name with joy confessing'),
(66, 3, 4, 'Let all the saints unite!'),
(66, 3, 5, 'Each heart its praise outpouring'),
(66, 3, 6, 'To Thee all praise above,'),
(66, 3, 7, 'Each voice in strains adoring'),
(66, 3, 8, 'Re-echoes - "God is love."'),
(67, 1, 1, 'We bless Thee, God and Father,'),
(67, 1, 2, 'We joy before Thy face;'),
(67, 1, 3, 'Beyond dark death for ever,'),
(67, 1, 4, 'We share Thy Son''s blest place.'),
(67, 1, 5, 'He lives a Man before Thee'),
(67, 1, 6, 'In cloudless light above,'),
(67, 1, 7, 'In Thine unbounded favour,'),
(67, 1, 8, 'Thine everlasting love.'),
(67, 2, 1, 'His Father and our Father,'),
(67, 2, 2, 'His God and ours Thou art;'),
(67, 2, 3, 'And He is Thy beloved,'),
(67, 2, 4, 'The gladness of Thy heart.'),
(67, 2, 5, 'We''re His, in joy He brings us'),
(67, 2, 6, 'To share His part and place,'),
(67, 2, 7, 'To know Thy love and favour,'),
(67, 2, 8, 'The shining of Thy face.'),
(67, 3, 1, 'Thy love that now enfolds us'),
(67, 3, 2, 'Can ne''er wax cold or dim;'),
(67, 3, 3, 'In Him that love doth centre,'),
(67, 3, 4, 'And we are loved in Him.'),
(67, 3, 5, 'In Him Thy love and glory'),
(67, 3, 6, 'Find their eternal rest;'),
(67, 3, 7, 'The many sons - His brethren -'),
(67, 3, 8, 'In Him, how near, how blest!'),
(68, 1, 1, 'O Lord of glory, who couldst leave'),
(68, 1, 2, 'The height supreme in death to lie,'),
(68, 1, 3, 'What tongue shall sing, what heart conceive'),
(68, 1, 4, 'The love divine that made Thee die?'),
(68, 1, 5, 'Bought with a price, for ever Thine,'),
(68, 1, 6, 'We bless Thee for Thy stoop divine.'),
