(112, 3, 2, 'In a servant''s form come near,'),
(112, 3, 3, 'Sitting, walking, talking with thee!'),
(112, 3, 4, 'Sinai''s mount no longer fear.'),
(112, 4, 1, 'Onward still to Calv''ry moving,'),
(112, 4, 2, 'Onward still He treads His way,'),
(112, 4, 3, 'God the Father''s will fulfilling,'),
(112, 4, 4, 'Love to sinners to display.'),
(112, 5, 1, 'Hearken to the wondrous story -'),
(112, 5, 2, 'Jesus died and rose for thee;'),
(112, 5, 3, 'God in heav''n now waits to save thee,'),
(112, 5, 4, 'And, believing, thou art free.'),
(113, 1, 1, 'Lord Jesus, come, Thy saints for Thee are waiting,'),
(113, 1, 2, 'To see Thy face and be with Thee at home;'),
(113, 1, 3, 'E''en now our endless bliss anticipating,'),
(113, 1, 4, 'With all our hearts we say, "Lord Jesus, come!"'),
(113, 2, 1, 'Lord  Jesus, come, our hearts for Thee are longing,'),
(113, 2, 2, 'To share Thy joy in those bright courts above,'),
(113, 2, 3, 'Where Thou wilt have Thy saints around Thee thronging,'),
(113, 2, 4, 'In all the blessed fulness of Thy love.'),
(113, 3, 1, 'Lord Jesus, come; with hearts and voices blending,'),
(113, 3, 2, 'Soon shall we praise Thee in Thy Father''s home;'),
(113, 3, 3, 'Soon shall we sing the new song, never ending,'),
(113, 3, 4, 'But now we sing to Thee, "Lord Jesus, come!"'),
(114, 1, 1, 'Lord Jesus, source of every grace,'),
(114, 1, 2, 'Glorious in light divine,'),
(114, 1, 3, 'Soon shall we see Thee face to face,'),
(114, 1, 4, 'And in that glory shine;'),
(114, 2, 1, 'Be ever with Thee, hear Thy voice,'),
(114, 2, 2, 'Unhindered then shall taste'),
(114, 2, 3, 'The love which doth our hearts rejoice,'),
(114, 2, 4, 'Though absent in this waste.'),
(114, 3, 1, 'In peaceful wonder we adore'),
(114, 3, 2, 'The thoughts of love divine,'),
(114, 3, 3, 'Which in that world, for evermore,'),
(114, 3, 4, 'Unite our lot with Thine.'),
(115, 1, 1, 'Lead on, almighty Lord,'),
(115, 1, 2, 'Lead on to victory;'),
(115, 1, 3, 'Encouraged by Thy blessed word,'),
(115, 1, 4, 'With joy we follow Thee.'),
(115, 2, 1, 'We follow Thee, our Guide,'),
(115, 2, 2, 'Who didst salvation bring;'),
(115, 2, 3, 'We follow Thee, through grace supplied'),
(115, 2, 4, 'From heav''n''s eternal spring:'),
(115, 3, 1, 'Till, of the prize possessed,'),
(115, 3, 2, 'We hear of war no more,'),
(115, 3, 3, 'And, O sweet thought! for ever rest'),
(115, 3, 4, 'On yonder peaceful shore.'),
(116, 1, 1, 'Blest God and father, we confess'),
(116, 1, 2, 'We every grace derive from Thee,'),
(116, 1, 3, 'And in Thy well-beloved Son'),
(116, 1, 4, 'Whose death secured our liberty.'),
(116, 2, 1, 'The Holy Spirit''s power reveals'),
(116, 2, 2, 'The things that to our peace belong;'),
(116, 2, 3, 'Here nothing ill can now intrude,'),
(116, 2, 4, 'Nor jarring notes disturb our song.'),
(116, 3, 1, 'How may we rise to Thy vast thoughts,'),
(116, 3, 2, 'Or apprehend Thy sovereign will -'),
(116, 3, 3, 'The grace that sets our souls on high,'),
(116, 3, 4, 'And love that brings us nearer still?'),
(116, 4, 1, 'Embraced in Thine unchanging love,'),
(116, 4, 2, 'Its holy stimulus doth serve'),
(116, 4, 3, 'To wake our richest songs of praise,'),
(116, 4, 4, 'And claim our hearts without reserve.'),
(116, 5, 1, 'O wondrous sphere! ''Tis vibrant now'),
(116, 5, 2, 'With one resounding note of joy'),
(116, 5, 3, 'From many sons who worship Thee -'),
(116, 5, 4, 'Eternity''s serene employ.'),
(116, 6, 1, 'Absorbed in favour all divine'),
(116, 6, 2, 'Conferred on those of high estate,'),
(116, 6, 3, 'Our hearts, surrend''ring unto Thee,'),
(116, 6, 4, 'Are held in love so full, so great.'),
(117, 1, 1, 'Lord, in past and distant ages,'),
(117, 1, 2, 'Long before the ken of man,'),
(117, 1, 3, 'Ere creation''s words were spoken,'),
(117, 1, 4, 'Or the heav''ns and earth began,'),
(117, 1, 5, 'Thou wast there in all Thy glory -'),
(117, 1, 6, 'Blessed Lord, we bow the knee -'),
(117, 1, 7, 'Dwelling then in love unbounded:'),
(117, 1, 8, 'Homage now we render Thee.'),
(117, 2, 1, 'What that love no thought can fathom;'),
(117, 2, 2, 'Nor can human lips define'),
(117, 2, 3, 'Those relationships eternal,'),
(117, 2, 4, 'All inscrutable, divine!'),
(117, 2, 5, 'But, in time, Thou wouldst in manhood'),
(117, 2, 6, 'Here the Name of God declare,'),
(117, 2, 7, 'In a wondrous, blest relation'),
(117, 2, 8, 'Which Thou couldst with others share.'),
(117, 3, 1, 'All His will Thou hast accomplished,'),
(117, 3, 2, 'All the work He gave Thee, done;'),
(117, 3, 3, 'One in thought, in plan and purpose,'),
(117, 3, 4, 'He the Father, Thou the Son.'),
(117, 3, 5, 'But on resurrection''s morning,'),
(117, 3, 6, 'To Thine own Thou didst declare'),
(117, 3, 7, 'That Thy Father was their Father,'),
(117, 3, 8, 'And His love they now might share.'),
(118, 1, 1, 'Glory be to God the Father,'),
(118, 1, 2, 'And to Christ the Son,'),
(118, 1, 3, 'Glory to the Holy Spirit -'),
(118, 1, 4, 'Ever One.'),
(118, 2, 1, 'As we view the vast creation,'),
(118, 2, 2, 'Planned with wondrous skill,'),
(118, 2, 3, 'So our minds would move to worship,'),
(118, 2, 4, 'And be still.'),
(118, 3, 1, 'But, our God, how great Thy yearning'),
(118, 3, 2, 'To have sons who love'),
(118, 3, 3, 'In Thy house e''en now to praise Thee,'),
(118, 3, 4, 'Then above!'),
(118, 4, 1, '''Twas Thy thought in revelation,'),
(118, 4, 2, 'To present to men'),
(118, 4, 3, 'Secrets of Thine own affections,'),
(118, 4, 4, 'Theirs to win.'),
(118, 5, 1, 'So in Christ, through His redemption'),
(118, 5, 2, '(Vanquished evil powers!),'),
(118, 5, 3, 'Thou hast brought, in new creation,'),
(118, 5, 4, 'Worshippers!'),
(118, 6, 1, 'Glory be to God the Father,'),
(118, 6, 2, 'And to Christ the Son,'),
(118, 6, 3, 'Glory to the Holy Spirit -'),
(118, 6, 4, 'Ever One.'),
(119, 1, 1, 'Our God and father, we draw near to Thee'),
(119, 1, 2, 'In all the worth of Thy beloved Son;'),
(119, 1, 3, 'All Thou hast e''er desired from man we see'),
(119, 1, 4, 'In Him, Thy Christ, Thine own anointed One.'),
(119, 2, 1, 'No thought of His e''er moved apart from Thine;'),
(119, 2, 2, 'Each holy footstep gave Thee fresh delight;'),
(119, 2, 3, 'Perfect expression of Thy will divine'),
(119, 2, 4, 'Thou hadst in Him - come forth from glory bright.'),
(119, 3, 1, 'Thou ever lovedst Him - ere time began'),
(119, 3, 2, 'He was beside Thee - one in all Thou art;'),
(119, 3, 3, 'In Godhead counsel one, in that vast plan'),
(119, 3, 4, 'In which Thou wouldst make known to men Thy heart.'),
(119, 4, 1, 'And now Thou lov''st Him, for Himself He gave -'),
(119, 4, 2, 'Theme of our song when time shall cease to be;'),
(119, 4, 3, 'Laid down His life that Thou, O God, shouldst have'),
(119, 4, 4, 'Fruit of Thy love in sons who worship Thee.'),
(120, 1, 1, 'Father, in Thine eternal power,');
INSERT INTO `hymn_line` (`hymn_no`, `vers_no`, `line_no`, `line_text`) VALUES (120, 1, 2, 'Thy grace and majesty divine,'),
(120, 1, 3, 'No soul, in this weak mortal hour,'),
(120, 1, 4, 'Can grasp the glory that is Thine!'),
(120, 2, 1, 'E''en in its thoughts of boundless grace'),
(120, 2, 2, 'It leaves us all far, far behind;'),
(120, 2, 3, 'The love that gives with Christ a place'),
(120, 2, 4, 'Surpasses our poor feeble mind!'),
(120, 3, 1, 'And yet that love is not unknown'),
(120, 3, 2, 'To those who have the Saviour seen;'),
(120, 3, 3, 'Nor strange to those He calls His own,'),
(120, 3, 4, 'Pilgrims in scenes where He has been.'),
(120, 4, 1, 'In Him Thy perfect love revealed'),
(120, 4, 2, 'Has led our hearts that love to trace,'),
(120, 4, 3, 'Where nothing of that love''s concealed,'),
(120, 4, 4, 'But meets us in our lowly place.'),
(120, 5, 1, 'And here we walk as sons, through grace,'),
(120, 5, 2, 'A Father''s love our present joy;'),
(120, 5, 3, 'Sons in the brightness of Thy face'),
(120, 5, 4, 'Find rest no sorrows can destroy!'),
(121, 1, 1, 'Blessed Spirit of the father,'),
(121, 1, 2, 'What a work has now been done'),
(121, 1, 3, 'By Thine own most glorious service'),
(121, 1, 4, 'For the Father and the Son!'),
(121, 1, 5, 'God''s great purpose Thou fulfillest'),
(121, 1, 6, 'In securing now the bride,'),
(121, 1, 7, 'And the Father''s thoughts in glory'),
(121, 1, 8, 'For His Son are satisfied.'),
(121, 2, 1, 'Thou dost know the Father''s feelings'),
(121, 2, 2, 'Of affection for His Son,'),
(121, 2, 3, 'And His joy in the assembly'),
(121, 2, 4, 'As united to that One.'),
(121, 2, 5, 'Thou art worthy of our praises'),
(121, 2, 6, 'As Thy power its strength imparts,'),
(121, 2, 7, 'That the Christ, the Head of all things,'),
(121, 2, 8, 'May through faith dwell in our hearts.'),
(122, 1, 1, 'Christ is the Saviour of sinners,'),
(122, 1, 2, 'Christ is the Saviour for me;'),
(122, 1, 3, 'Long I was chained in sin''s darkness,'),
(122, 1, 4, 'Now by His grace I am free.'),
(122, 2, 1, 'Saviour of sinners,'),
(122, 2, 2, 'Saviour of sinners like me,'),
