(122, 2, 4, 'This is the Saviour for me.'),
(122, 3, 1, 'Now I can say I am pardoned,'),
(122, 3, 2, 'Happy and justified, free,'),
(122, 3, 3, 'Saved by my blessed Redeemer -'),
(122, 3, 4, 'This is the Saviour for me.'),
(122, 4, 1, 'Just as I was He received me,'),
(122, 4, 2, 'Seeking from judgment to flee;'),
(122, 4, 3, 'Now there is no condemnation -'),
(122, 4, 4, 'This is the Saviour for me.'),
(122, 5, 1, 'Loved with a love that''s unchanging,'),
(122, 5, 2, 'Blessed with all blessings so free,'),
(122, 5, 3, 'How shall I tell out His praises!'),
(122, 5, 4, 'This is the Saviour for me.'),
(122, 6, 1, 'Soon shall the glory be dawning,'),
(122, 6, 2, 'Then, when His face I shall see,'),
(122, 6, 3, 'Sing, O my soul, in thy gladness,'),
(122, 6, 4, 'This is the Saviour for me!'),
(123, 1, 1, 'God waits in grace with hands outstretched to bless -'),
(123, 1, 2, 'Glad news from heav''n!'),
