(129, 1, 1, '"Thou art that God" to the ages eternal,'),
(129, 1, 2, 'Loved and adored by blest myriads of men!'),
(129, 1, 3, 'Feeling the warmth of affections paternal,'),
(129, 1, 4, 'Fam''lies predestined shall fill earth and heav''n.'),
(129, 2, 1, 'Strengthened with might by the Father''s own Spirit,'),
(129, 2, 2, 'We now by faith hold the Christ in our heart;'),
(129, 2, 3, 'Thus apprehending a sphere vast, yet finite,'),
(129, 2, 4, 'Love of the Christ passing knowledge our part.'),
(129, 3, 1, 'Thou canst, O God, even fill to Thy fullness'),
(129, 3, 2, 'Hearts which are stirred by this wonderful theme;'),
(129, 3, 3, 'In the assembly, now blest in Christ Jesus,'),
(129, 3, 4, 'Be to Thee endlessly glory supreme!'),
(130, 1, 1, 'Father, to Thee we now draw near,'),
(130, 1, 2, 'With Christ, the Firstborn, to appear,'),
(130, 1, 3, 'The double portion we enjoy,'),
(130, 1, 4, 'While endless praise our lips employ'),
(130, 1, 5, 'And "Abba Father!" cry.'),
(130, 2, 1, 'O love so great, so full, so free,'),
(130, 2, 2, 'That leads, blest Father, now to Thee,'),
(130, 2, 3, 'Thy Spirit strength''ning in our heart,'),
(130, 2, 4, 'With Christ to know our heav''nly part,'),
(130, 2, 5, 'And glory give to Thee.'),
(131, 1, 1, 'O Lord, with our ears and hearts open,'),
(131, 1, 2, 'Awaiting Thy shout would we be,'),
(131, 1, 3, 'The summons that calls us to heaven,'),
(131, 1, 4, 'For ever to be Lord, with Thee.'),
(131, 1, 5, 'Thy word and Thy Spirit, blest Lover,'),
(131, 1, 6, 'The earnest, are giv''n to Thy bride;'),
(131, 1, 7, 'Thou''rt near to faith''s vision, O Saviour,'),
(131, 1, 8, 'But soon she will be at Thy side.'),
(131, 2, 1, 'O come then, lord Jesus, we''re watching!'),
(131, 2, 2, 'And take now Thy spouse home to Thee!'),
