(131, 3, 4, 'To see Thee, her faithful Bridegroom.'),
(131, 3, 5, 'Gross darkness the earth doth now cover,'),
(131, 3, 6, 'And night like a pall shrouds the land;'),
(131, 3, 7, 'Thy flock is still here, Shepherd Lover,'),
(131, 3, 8, 'The sheep Thou hast kept by Thy hand.'),
(131, 4, 1, 'Midst darkness faith clearly sees beaming'),
