(134, 1, 6, 'The charm of Thine own grace.'),
(134, 1, 7, 'Enraptured by Thy beauty,'),
(134, 1, 8, 'We gaze upon Thy face.'),
(134, 2, 1, 'How fair is Thy companion!'),
(134, 2, 2, 'How pleasing in Thy sight!'),
(134, 2, 3, 'To be Thy joy for ever,'),
(134, 2, 4, 'Object of Thy delight;'),
(134, 2, 5, 'Fruit of Thine own blest service,'),
