(154, 1, 5, 'On the cross He once has suffered,'),
(154, 1, 6, 'There by Him the work was done;'),
(154, 1, 7, 'And the word by God now uttered'),
(154, 1, 8, 'To each weary soul is - Come!'),
(154, 2, 1, 'Come! - the Father''s house stands open,'),
(154, 2, 2, 'With its love and light and song;'),
(154, 2, 3, 'And returning to that Father,'),
(154, 2, 4, 'All to you may now belong.'),
(154, 2, 5, 'From sin''s distant land of famine,'),
(154, 2, 6, 'Toiling ''neath the mid-day sun,'),
(154, 2, 7, 'To a Father''s house of plenty,'),
(154, 2, 8, 'And a Father''s welcome, Come!'),
(154, 3, 1, 'Come! - for night is gath''ring quickly'),
(154, 3, 2, 'O''er this world''s fast fleeting day;'),
(154, 3, 3, 'If you linger in the darkness,'),
(154, 3, 4, 'You will surely miss your way.'),
(154, 3, 5, 'From the world and its delusion -'),
(154, 3, 6, 'Now our voices rise as one,'),
(154, 3, 7, 'While we give God''s invitation;'),
(154, 3, 8, 'Heav''n itself re-echoes - Come!'),
(155, 1, 1, 'What was it, blessed God,'),
(155, 1, 2, 'Led Thee to give Thy Son,'),
(155, 1, 3, 'To yield Thy Well-beloved'),
(155, 1, 4, 'For us by sin undone?'),
(155, 1, 5, '''Twas love unbounded led Thee thus'),
(155, 1, 6, 'To give Thy Well-beloved for us.'),
(155, 2, 1, 'What led Thy Son, O God,'),
(155, 2, 2, 'To come from heav''n on high,'),
(155, 2, 3, 'To shed His precious blood,'),
(155, 2, 4, 'To suffer and to die?'),
(155, 2, 5, '''Twas love, unbounded love to us,'),
(155, 2, 6, 'Led Him to die and suffer thus.'),
(155, 3, 1, 'What moved Thee to impart'),
(155, 3, 2, 'Thy Spirit from above,'),
(155, 3, 3, 'Therewith to fill our heart'),
(155, 3, 4, 'With heav''nly peace and love?'),
(155, 3, 5, '''Twas love, unbounded love to us,'),
(155, 3, 6, 'Moved Thee to give Thy Spirit thus.'),
(155, 4, 1, 'What love to Thee we owe,'),
(155, 4, 2, 'Our God, for all Thy grace!'),
(155, 4, 3, 'Our hearts may well outflow'),
(155, 4, 4, 'In everlasting praise.'),
(155, 4, 5, 'Gladly, O God, we praise Thee thus'),
(155, 4, 6, 'For all Thy boundless love to us.'),
(156, 1, 1, 'Blessed Lord, our hallelujahs'),
(156, 1, 2, 'Now to Thee we raise;'),
(156, 1, 3, 'Never could we fully utter'),
(156, 1, 4, 'All Thy worth and praise.'),
(156, 1, 5, 'Praise the Lamb! yes, Thou art worthy,'),
(156, 1, 6, 'Who didst shed Thy blood'),
(156, 1, 7, 'To redeem Thy saints and make us'),
(156, 1, 8, 'Kings and priests to God.'),
(156, 2, 1, 'Yes, we praise Thee, for Thou lov''st us;'),
(156, 2, 2, 'And we bless Thee, Lord,'),
(156, 2, 3, 'For the peace and joy and gladness'),
(156, 2, 4, 'Which Thou dost afford.'),
(156, 2, 5, 'Hallelujah! Thou, Lord Jesus,'),
(156, 2, 6, 'Canst not cease to love;'),
(156, 2, 7, 'Thine we are, and Thine for ever,'),
(156, 2, 8, 'One with Thee above.'),
(156, 3, 1, 'Praise the Lord! Yes, hallelujah!'),
(156, 3, 2, 'Who would hush the song?'),
(156, 3, 3, 'Join with saints from every nation,'),
(156, 3, 4, 'Every tribe and tongue.'),
(156, 3, 5, 'Praise the Lamb, for He is worthy,'),
(156, 3, 6, 'Sweet eternal strain!'),
(156, 3, 7, 'Hallelujah! Hallelujah!'),
(156, 3, 8, 'Praise the Lord! Amen.'),
(157, 1, 1, 'We worship Thee, O God,'),
(157, 1, 2, 'And praise Thy matchless grace;'),
(157, 1, 3, 'Our adoration bring,'),
(157, 1, 4, 'And bow before Thy face.'),
(157, 1, 5, 'Thy Son hath brought Thy love to light;'),
(157, 1, 6, 'In songs of joy we now unite.'),
(157, 2, 1, 'Accepted in Thy Son,'),
(157, 2, 2, 'We "Abba, Father!" cry;'),
(157, 2, 3, 'Through Him Thy love is known,'),
(157, 2, 4, 'In Him we are brought nigh.'),
(157, 2, 5, 'With rev''rence and with love we bow'),
(157, 2, 6, 'To Thee, O God, our Father Thou!'),
(158, 1, 1, 'Blest Spirit, Comforter divine,'),
(158, 1, 2, 'We seek Thy gracious help this hour;'),
(158, 1, 3, 'Give us to hear Thy voice benign,'),
(158, 1, 4, 'Cause us afresh to prove Thy power.'),
(158, 2, 1, 'Searcher of depths, the depths of God,'),
(158, 2, 2, 'Dispenser Thou of heaven''s store;'),
(158, 2, 3, 'To us, our Guide, fresh grace afford,'),
(158, 2, 4, 'As love''s domain our hearts explore.'),
(158, 3, 1, 'With every thought by Thee controlled,'),
(158, 3, 2, 'The truth''s pure light would we pursue,'),
(158, 3, 3, 'As Thou, blest Spirit, dost unfold'),
(158, 3, 4, 'Eternal glories to our view.'),
(159, 1, 1, 'Lord Jesus, Thou hast drawn our hearts,'),
(159, 1, 2, 'That we might near Thee be;'),
(159, 1, 3, 'Thy bride, the object of Thy love -'),
(159, 1, 4, 'We thus are one with Thee.'),
(159, 2, 1, 'O wondrous joy in union found,'),
(159, 2, 2, 'Thou all in all to us!'),
(159, 2, 3, 'Thy holy love fills every heart -'),
(159, 2, 4, 'Thy joy to have it thus.'),
(159, 3, 1, 'To be for Thee, O Lord, what bliss'),
(159, 3, 2, 'No human tongue can tell!'),
(159, 3, 3, 'The movements of such love as this'),
(159, 3, 4, 'Responsive songs impel.'),
(160, 1, 1, 'O bright and blessed hope!'),
(160, 1, 2, 'When shall it be'),
(160, 1, 3, 'That we His face, long loved,'),
(160, 1, 4, 'Revealed shall see?'),
(160, 2, 1, 'O when, without a cloud,'),
(160, 2, 2, 'His features trace,'),
(160, 2, 3, 'Whose faithful love so long'),
(160, 2, 4, 'We''ve known in grace;'),
(160, 3, 1, 'That love itself enjoy,'),
(160, 3, 2, 'Which, ever true,'),
(160, 3, 3, 'Did in our feeble path'),
(160, 3, 4, 'Its work pursue?'),
(160, 4, 1, 'O Jesus! not unknown,'),
(160, 4, 2, 'Thy love shall fill'),
(160, 4, 3, 'The heart in which Thou dwell''st,'),
(160, 4, 4, 'And shalt dwell still.'),
(160, 5, 1, 'Still, Lord, to see Thy face,'),
(160, 5, 2, 'Thy voice to hear;'),
(160, 5, 3, 'To know Thy present love,'),
(160, 5, 4, 'For ever near;'),
(160, 6, 1, 'To gaze upon Thyself'),
(160, 6, 2, 'So faithful known,'),
(160, 6, 3, 'Long proved in secret help'),
(160, 6, 4, 'With Thee alone;'),
(160, 7, 1, 'To see that love, content,'),
(160, 7, 2, 'On us flow forth,'),
(160, 7, 3, 'For ever Thy delight,'),
(160, 7, 4, 'Clothed with Thy worth!'),
(160, 8, 1, 'Nor what is next Thy heart'),
(160, 8, 2, 'Can we forget;'),
(160, 8, 3, 'Thy saints, O Lord, with Thee'),
(160, 8, 4, 'In glory met.'),
(160, 9, 1, 'Perfect in comeliness'),
(160, 9, 2, 'Before Thy face,'),
(160, 9, 3, 'Th''eternal witness, all,'),
(160, 9, 4, 'Of Thine own grace;'),
(160, 10, 1, 'Together then their songs'),
(160, 10, 2, 'Of endless praise,'),
(160, 10, 3, 'With one harmonious voice,'),
(160, 10, 4, 'In joy they''ll raise!'),
(161, 1, 1, 'Son of God, with joy we view Thee'),
(161, 1, 2, 'Of God''s love the object meet;'),
(161, 1, 3, 'While, Lord Jesus Christ, ''tis through Thee'),
(161, 1, 4, 'All our blessing is complete.'),
(161, 2, 1, 'As Thy brethren now we hail Thee,'),
(161, 2, 2, 'Firstborn of a heav''nly race;'),
(161, 2, 3, 'He who has with glory crowned Thee'),
(161, 2, 4, 'Called us to this blessed place.'),
(161, 3, 1, 'From the triumph and the glory'),
(161, 3, 2, 'Of Thy rest in love divine,'),
(161, 3, 3, 'Comes to us the wondrous story,'),
(161, 3, 4, 'How God''s purpose made us Thine;'),
(161, 4, 1, 'How by dying Thou hast freed us'),
(161, 4, 2, 'From the man of sin and shame,'),
(161, 4, 3, 'That, unhindered, Thou mightst lead us'),
(161, 4, 4, 'Now to know Thy Father''s name.'),
(161, 5, 1, 'And, responsive to Thy longing,'),
(161, 5, 2, 'We would now abide in love;'),
(161, 5, 3, 'Know Thy joy, as those belonging'),
(161, 5, 4, 'To Thyself in heav''n above.'),
(161, 6, 1, 'Thus in holy adoration'),
(161, 6, 2, 'At Thy feet our hearts would bow,'),
(161, 6, 3, 'Who hast brought, in new creation,'),
(161, 6, 4, 'Sons of God before Him now.'),
(161, 7, 1, 'And a song is sweetly thrilling'),
(161, 7, 2, 'Every heart within the shrine:'),
(161, 7, 3, 'Music which God''s ear is filling,'),
(161, 7, 4, 'Notes which could be only Thine.'),
(162, 1, 1, 'God our Father, Thee we worship,'),
(162, 1, 2, 'Own the glory of Thy grace;'),
(162, 1, 3, 'Joying in Thy sovereign purpose'),
(162, 1, 4, 'That with Christ should be our place.'),
(162, 2, 1, 'Abba, Father! He who knows Thee'),
(162, 2, 2, 'Has Thy Name to us declared;'),
(162, 2, 3, 'And Thy love for Him unchanging,'),
(162, 2, 4, 'By Thy many sons is shared.'),
(162, 3, 1, 'Now Thy glory is before us, -'),
(162, 3, 2, 'Fam''lies named by Thee alone, -'),
(162, 3, 3, 'We, the firstborn ones, adore Thee,'),
(162, 3, 4, 'Bless Thee, as in Christ made known!'),
(163, 1, 1, '"Yet a little while," Thou''rt coming!'),
(163, 1, 2, 'All Thine own this promise share;'),
(163, 1, 3, 'Patience waits, while love is yearning'),
(163, 1, 4, 'For Thy presence in the air.'),
(163, 1, 5, 'Sleeping ones will rise immortal,'),
(163, 1, 6, 'And the living changed shall be'),
(163, 1, 7, 'When, caught up through glory''s portal,'),
(163, 1, 8, 'We our blessed Saviour see.'),
(163, 2, 1, 'As Thou art in heav''nly glory,'),
(163, 2, 2, 'Thine own image we shall bear -'),
(163, 2, 3, 'Blessed climax of love''s story -'),
(163, 2, 4, 'And Thy throne and kingdom share.'),
(163, 2, 5, 'O what bliss - eternal pleasure -'),
(163, 2, 6, 'With Thee evermore to be!'),
(163, 2, 7, 'Filled with joy beyond all measure'),
(163, 2, 8, 'When Thy glorious face we see!'),
(164, 1, 1, 'Jesus, our Lord, we assemble together,'),
(164, 1, 2, 'Here to remember Thyself whom we love,'),
(164, 1, 3, 'For as Thine own we are feeling Thine absence,'),
(164, 1, 4, 'Though we delight in Thy glory above.'),
(164, 2, 1, 'Now, Lord, together in blessed communion,'),
(164, 2, 2, 'Praise we Thy Name as Thyself we await.'),
(164, 2, 3, 'Soon shalt Thou take Thine appointed dominion,'),
(164, 2, 4, 'Soon shalt appear in Thy royal estate.'),
(164, 3, 1, 'Till Thine outshining Thy death we are showing,'),
(164, 3, 2, 'Owning Thee thus as the One without peer;'),
(164, 3, 3, 'Whilst, lord, that death of such shame and deep suff''ring'),
(164, 3, 4, 'Unto Thy lovers Thyself doth endear.'),
(164, 4, 1, 'For Thou hast loved us with love never failing,'),
(164, 4, 2, 'Laid down Thy life for us, given Thine all.'),
(164, 4, 3, 'Love strong as death has been proved and has triumphed,'),
(164, 4, 4, 'Love which our hearts shall for ever enthrall.'),
(165, 1, 1, '''Tis not far off - the hour'),
(165, 1, 2, 'When Christ will claim His own;'),
(165, 1, 3, 'We soon shall hear that voice of power;'),
(165, 1, 4, 'The Lord Himself shall come!'),
(165, 2, 1, 'The days are passing by,'),
(165, 2, 2, 'The years flow on apace;'),
(165, 2, 3, 'Lord Jesus, Thy return draws nigh,'),
(165, 2, 4, 'We long to see Thy face.'),
(165, 3, 1, 'Eternal in the heav''ns'),
(165, 3, 2, 'Is our prepared abode -'),
(165, 3, 3, 'Radiant and pure, in light divine,'),
(165, 3, 4, 'The building of our God.'),
(165, 4, 1, 'Then rest, divinely sweet,'),
(165, 4, 2, 'Our pilgrim feet shall know;'),
(165, 4, 3, 'And through that blest eternity'),
(165, 4, 4, 'What tides of praise shall flow!'),
(165, 5, 1, 'In patience, Lord, we wait'),
(165, 5, 2, 'For Thee to take us home;'),
(165, 5, 3, 'Fulfil to us Thy gracious word.'),
(165, 5, 4, 'Amen, Lord Jesus, Come!'),
(166, 1, 1, 'From scenes of conflict, burden, grief and care,'),
(166, 1, 2, 'To Thy blest presence, Lord, we now repair;'),
(166, 1, 3, 'Thy shadow here provides a calm retreat,'),
(166, 1, 4, 'Where sympathies divine our frailty meet.'),
(166, 2, 1, 'To Thee the cause of every sigh is known,'),
(166, 2, 2, 'Thou who dost feel the sorrows of Thine own;'),
(166, 2, 3, 'Unspoken fears, and questions hard to solve,'),
(166, 2, 4, 'Before the rays of heav''nly light dissolve.'),
(166, 3, 1, 'Thy well-proved love our confidence inspires'),
(166, 3, 2, 'To count upon the grace that never tires;'),
(166, 3, 3, 'So would we make Thine interests, Lord, our care,'),
(166, 3, 4, 'And with thanksgiving wait on Thee in prayer.'),
(167, 1, 1, 'Precious, precious blood of Jesus,'),
(167, 1, 2, 'Shed on Calvary!'),
(167, 1, 3, 'Shed for rebels, shed for sinners,'),
(167, 1, 4, 'Shed for me.'),
(167, 2, 1, 'Precious, precious blood of Jesus!'),
(167, 2, 2, 'All the price is paid;'),
(167, 2, 3, 'Perfect pardon now is offered,'),
(167, 2, 4, 'Peace is made.'),
(167, 3, 1, 'Precious, precious blood of Jesus,'),
(167, 3, 2, 'Jesus. God''s own Son!'),
(167, 3, 3, 'Telling that the work is finished;'),
(167, 3, 4, 'All is done.'),
(167, 4, 1, 'Thought Thy sins are red like crimson,'),
(167, 4, 2, 'Deep in scarlet glow,'),
(167, 4, 3, 'Jesus'' precious blood can make them'),
(167, 4, 4, 'White as snow.'),
(167, 5, 1, 'Precious blood, whose full atonement'),
(167, 5, 2, 'Bringeth us to God!'),
(167, 5, 3, 'Precious blood, our song and glory,'),
(167, 5, 4, 'Praise and laud!'),
(168, 1, 1, 'O blessed God, we praise Thee,'),
(168, 1, 2, 'In wisdom hast Thou planned'),
(168, 1, 3, 'A universe of glory,'),
(168, 1, 4, 'Beyond the changing sand'),
(168, 1, 5, 'Of time - where men immortal,'),
(168, 1, 6, 'Should dwell in radiant light;'),
(168, 1, 7, 'And creature with Creator,'),
(168, 1, 8, 'In Thine own realm delight.'),
(168, 2, 1, 'From out those mighty counsels'),
(168, 2, 2, 'What treasures have been shown!'),
(168, 2, 3, 'Thy choicest thoughts in purpose,'),
(168, 2, 4, 'Before the worlds were known -'),
(168, 2, 5, 'That we, in Christ, before Thee,'),
(168, 2, 6, 'Should share the Son''s blest place;'),
(168, 2, 7, 'Enjoy, in cloudless favour,'),
(168, 2, 8, 'The riches of Thy grace.'),
(168, 3, 1, 'And soon this sonship glory -'),
(168, 3, 2, 'Secured in wisdom''s way -'),
(168, 3, 3, 'Shall be our endless portion'),
(168, 3, 4, 'In that eternal day.'),
(168, 3, 5, 'So gladly now responsive'),
(168, 3, 6, 'Our voices we would raise;'),
(168, 3, 7, 'Blest Father, Son and Spirit'),
(168, 3, 8, 'To Thee be endless praise!'),
(169, 1, 1, 'O what a Saviour is Jesus the Lord!'),
(169, 1, 2, 'Well may His Name by His saints be adored!'),
(169, 1, 3, 'He has redeemed them from hell by His blood,'),
(169, 1, 4, 'Saved them for ever, and brought them to God.'),
(169, 2, 1, 'Now in the glory He waits to impart'),
(169, 2, 2, 'Peace to the conscience, and joy to the heart;'),
(169, 2, 3, 'Waits to be gracious, to pardon and heal'),
(169, 2, 4, 'All who their sin and their wretchedness feel.'),
(169, 3, 1, 'Thousands have fled to His spear-pierced side;'),
(169, 3, 2, 'Welcome they all have been, none are denied;'),
(169, 3, 3, 'Weary and laden, they all have been blest;'),
(169, 3, 4, 'Joyfully now in the Saviour they rest.'),
(170, 1, 1, 'Blessed God, with Christ before Thee'),
(170, 1, 2, 'We approach, in love set free;'),
(170, 1, 3, 'The assembly in Christ Jesus'),
(170, 1, 4, 'Yieldeth glory unto Thee.'),
(170, 2, 1, 'This - the product of Thy counsels,'),
(170, 2, 2, 'Rich with heav''nly beauties dressed,'),
(170, 2, 3, 'Formed to praise throughout the ages -'),
(170, 2, 4, 'In Thy presence is at rest.'),
(170, 3, 1, 'Vessel filled e''en to Thy fulness,'),
(170, 3, 2, 'And replete with radiance bright,'),
(170, 3, 3, 'In Thine own domain of glory'),
(170, 3, 4, 'Fills Thy heart with deep delight.'),
(171, 1, 1, 'Blest Son of God, we worship Thee;'),
(171, 1, 2, 'Thou lovest to draw near'),
(171, 1, 3, 'To hearts that wait for Thee alone'),
(171, 1, 4, 'And feel Thine absence here.'),
(171, 2, 1, 'Thou camest in of old and all'),
(171, 2, 2, 'The heav''nly hosts were stirred,'),
(171, 2, 3, 'And now amidst Thine own Thy praise'),
(171, 2, 4, 'Unceasingly is heard.'),
(171, 3, 1, 'Thou hast a glory far beyond'),
(171, 3, 2, 'The creature''s power to tell,'),
(171, 3, 3, 'Yet pleased to come, as lowly Man,'),
(171, 3, 4, '''Mid human hearts to dwell.'),
(171, 4, 1, 'Thou hast come in on God''s behalf'),
(171, 4, 2, 'To crown His wondrous ways,'),
(171, 4, 3, 'Firstborn of all to lead the throng'),
(171, 4, 4, 'In His eternal praise.'),
(171, 5, 1, 'We praise and worship as we see'),
(171, 5, 2, 'Thy glory spread abroad,'),
(171, 5, 3, 'And love that, giving all, secures'),
(171, 5, 4, 'The universe for God.'),
(172, 1, 1, 'O teach us more of Thy blest ways,'),
(172, 1, 2, 'Thou holy Lamb of God!'),
(172, 1, 3, 'And fix and root us in Thy grace,'),
(172, 1, 4, 'As those redeemed by blood.'),
(172, 2, 1, 'O tell us often of Thy love,'),
(172, 2, 2, 'Of all Thy grief and pain;'),
(172, 2, 3, 'And let our hearts with joy confess'),
(172, 2, 4, 'That thence comes all our gain.'),
(172, 3, 1, 'For this, O may we freely count'),
(172, 3, 2, 'Vain things of earth but dross;'),
(172, 3, 3, 'The dearest object of our love,'),
(172, 3, 4, 'Apart from Thee, but loss.'),
(172, 4, 1, 'Engrave this deeply on our hearts'),
(172, 4, 2, 'With an eternal pen,'),
(172, 4, 3, 'That we may, in a fuller way,'),
(172, 4, 4, 'Return Thy love again.'),
(173, 1, 1, 'Thou dwellest now, O God, midst fragrant praise'),
(173, 1, 2, 'Resulting from Thine own great work and ways;'),
(173, 1, 3, 'Th''assembly in Christ Jesus - ever blest,'),
(173, 1, 4, 'And filled to all Thy fulness - is at rest.'),
(173, 2, 1, 'In the Beloved favour now is known'),
(173, 2, 2, 'By her whom Christ can call with joy His own;'),
(173, 2, 3, 'For whom in love He gave Himself - His bride -'),
(173, 2, 4, 'To be with Him in glory, by His side:'),
(173, 3, 1, 'Perpetual freshness marks th''eternal day,'),
(173, 3, 2, 'Abiding peace, joy ne''er to fade away;'),
(173, 3, 3, 'Off''rings for God are in abundance brought,'),
(173, 3, 4, 'Willing response for all that Thou hast wrought.'),
(174, 1, 1, 'O patient, spotless One,'),
(174, 1, 2, 'Our hearts in meekness train'),
(174, 1, 3, 'To bear Thy yoke, and learn from Thee,'),
(174, 1, 4, 'That we may rest obtain.'),
(174, 2, 1, 'Jesus! Thou art enough'),
(174, 2, 2, 'The mind and heart to fill;'),
(174, 2, 3, 'Thy patient life - to calm the soul;'),
(174, 2, 4, 'Thy love - its fear dispel.'),
(174, 3, 1, 'O fix our earnest gaze'),
(174, 3, 2, 'So wholly, Lord, on Thee,'),
(174, 3, 3, 'That, with Thy beauty occupied,'),
(174, 3, 4, 'We elsewhere none may see.'),
(175, 1, 1, 'Everlasting glory unto Jesus be!'),
(175, 1, 2, 'Sing aloud the story of His victory!'),
(175, 1, 3, 'How He left the splendour of His home on high,'),
(175, 1, 4, 'Came in love so tender, on the cross to die.');
INSERT INTO `hymn_line` (`hymn_no`, `vers_no`, `line_no`, `line_text`) VALUES (175, 2, 1, 'Yes! He came from heaven, suffered in our stead;'),
(175, 2, 2, 'Praise to Him be given, Firstborn from the dead!'),
(175, 2, 3, 'Jesus, meek and lowly, came the lost to save;'),
(175, 2, 4, 'He, the Victim holy, triumphed o''er the grave.'),
(175, 3, 1, 'Christ is Lord of glory, sing we now today.'),
(175, 3, 2, 'Tell abroad the story; own His rightful sway!'),
(175, 3, 3, 'Sing aloud, and never cease to spread His fame;'),
(175, 3, 4, 'Triumph, now and ever, in the Saviour''s name.'),
(176, 1, 1, 'Blessed Lord, in love unceasing'),
(176, 1, 2, 'Thou dost live to intercede;'),
(176, 1, 3, 'Till Thou comest, Thou art serving'),
(176, 1, 4, 'All Thine own in time of need.'),
(176, 1, 5, 'Wonderful and gracious service,'),
(176, 1, 6, 'Love that bears us all the way'),
(176, 1, 7, 'On Thine arm, until we enter'),
(176, 1, 8, 'On that glorious, endless day!'),
(176, 2, 1, 'Thou appearest for Thy brethren,'),
(176, 2, 2, 'Till the pilgrim path is done;'),
(176, 2, 3, 'Never can we be forgotten,'),
(176, 2, 4, 'Thou wilt guide us safely home.'),
(176, 2, 5, 'What thought storms may rage against us?'),
(176, 2, 6, 'Nought can part us from Thy love!'),
(176, 2, 7, 'Well we know Thy hands uplifted -'),
(176, 2, 8, 'Thou art on the throne above.'),
(177, 1, 1, 'O wilt thou to the Saviour come?'),
(177, 1, 2, 'This hour He waits for thee,'),
(177, 1, 3, 'To cleanse Thy conscience, fill Thy heart,'),
(177, 1, 4, 'Thy captive soul set free.'),
(177, 2, 1, 'Let not Thy sins keep thee away,'),
(177, 2, 2, 'Since on the cross He died;'),
(177, 2, 3, 'And from the dead was raised that we'),
(177, 2, 4, 'Might now be justified.'),
(177, 3, 1, 'O see Him there at God''s right hand,'),
(177, 3, 2, 'made Lord and Christ above!'),
(177, 3, 3, 'Redemption''s finished work ensures'),
(177, 3, 4, 'That thou His grace canst prove.'),
(177, 4, 1, 'Whate''er thy need He''ll meet it now,'),
(177, 4, 2, 'In Him thou canst confide;'),
(177, 4, 3, 'Take from His hand the blessing free,'),
