(219, 1, 5, 'O this precious light is telling'),
(219, 1, 6, 'God''s full favour now to man;'),
(219, 1, 7, 'From the glory it is streaming -'),
(219, 1, 8, 'Ne''er such news since time began!'),
(219, 2, 1, 'God has full delight in Jesus,'),
(219, 2, 2, 'Brightest glory He has won;'),
(219, 2, 3, 'He has died, and through His dying'),
(219, 2, 4, 'All God''s pleasure will be done.'),
(219, 2, 5, 'O what blessing in believing'),
(219, 2, 6, 'In the One who came to die,'),
(219, 2, 7, 'And the glorious light receiving'),
(219, 2, 8, 'Of God''s Son enthroned on high!'),
(219, 3, 1, 'God has given all to Jesus,'),
(219, 3, 2, 'All shall prosper in His hand;'),
(219, 3, 3, 'Every knee shall bow to Jesus,'),
(219, 3, 4, 'All obey God''s own command.'),
(219, 3, 5, 'Come, then, trust this peerless Saviour,'),
(219, 3, 6, 'Prove the riches of His grace;'),
(219, 3, 7, 'Live for ever in God''s favour'),
(219, 3, 8, 'As it shines in Jesus face!'),
(220, 1, 1, 'I could not do without Thee,'),
(220, 1, 2, 'O Saviour of the lost,'),
(220, 1, 3, 'Whose precious blood redeemed me'),
(220, 1, 4, 'At such tremendous cost!'),
(220, 1, 5, 'Thy righteousness, Thy pardon,'),
(220, 1, 6, 'Thy precious blood must be'),
(220, 1, 7, 'My only hope and comfort,'),
(220, 1, 8, 'My glory and my plea!'),
(220, 2, 1, 'Why will you do without Him?'),
(220, 2, 2, 'The word of God is true:'),
(220, 2, 3, 'The world to doom is passing,'),
(220, 2, 4, 'And you are passing too.'),
(220, 2, 5, 'It may be no tomorrow'),
(220, 2, 6, 'Shall dawn on you or me;'),
(220, 2, 7, 'Why will you risk the peril'),
(220, 2, 8, 'Of lost eternity?'),
(220, 3, 1, 'But with Him - O with Jesus!'),
(220, 3, 2, 'Are any words so blest?'),
(220, 3, 3, 'With Jesus, joy unending,'),
(220, 3, 4, 'And everlasting rest!'),
(220, 3, 5, 'With Jesus - hearts now empty'),
(220, 3, 6, 'Filled with His perfect love;'),
(220, 3, 7, 'His perfect peace each moment,'),
(220, 3, 8, 'Till perfect bliss above.'),
(221, 1, 1, 'Jerusalem, the holy,'),
(221, 1, 2, 'Whose builder is her God,'),
(221, 1, 3, 'Resplendent with His glory'),
(221, 1, 4, 'Her shining spreads abroad;'),
(221, 1, 5, 'Descending out of heaven'),
(221, 1, 6, 'To fill with Christ in grace,'),
(221, 1, 7, 'In blest administration,'),
(221, 1, 8, 'As bride and wife, her place!'),
(221, 2, 1, 'Jerusalem, eternal!'),
(221, 2, 2, 'The city of Christ''s God,'),
(221, 2, 3, 'Thine origin celestial,'),
(221, 2, 4, 'Thou art His blest abode;'),
(221, 2, 5, 'Thy beauty all adorning'),
(221, 2, 6, 'For Him whose bride Thou art,'),
(221, 2, 7, 'To fill with joy unfading,'),
(221, 2, 8, 'With Christ, thine endless part!'),
(221, 3, 1, 'O residence of glory!'),
(221, 3, 2, 'God''s tabernacle then,'),
(221, 3, 3, 'Where He - O wondrous story -'),
(221, 3, 4, 'Doth dwell so near to men;'),
(221, 3, 5, 'Where new creation''s splendour'),
(221, 3, 6, 'Doth hold our raptured gaze,'),
(221, 3, 7, 'Kept by the Spirit''s power,'),
(221, 3, 8, 'And moved by Christ to praise!'),
(221, 4, 1, 'The Father, source of glory -'),
(221, 4, 2, 'The Son, the centre blest -'),
(221, 4, 3, 'The Spirit all pervading -'),
(221, 4, 4, 'The Fulness pleased, at rest!'),
(221, 4, 5, 'O God supreme, we bless Thee,'),
(221, 4, 6, 'And praise Thy glorious Name,'),
(221, 4, 7, 'For of Thee, through Thee, for Thee'),
(221, 4, 8, 'Are all things now, Amen.'),
(222, 1, 1, 'O Thou blessed Holy Spirit,'),
(222, 1, 2, 'Now our praise we sing to Thee.'),
(222, 1, 3, 'Heaven''s joys, which Thou hast taught us,'),
(222, 1, 4, 'Will abide eternally.'),
(222, 2, 1, 'As we contemplate Thy glory'),
(222, 2, 2, 'In Thy lowly service here,'),
(222, 2, 3, 'We would bow our hearts in homage,'),
(222, 2, 4, 'And Thy Deity revere.'),
(222, 3, 1, 'O we wonder at Thy patience!'),
(222, 3, 2, 'Precious is Thy presence here;'),
(222, 3, 3, 'Spirit, Thou, of truth, who leadest'),
(222, 3, 4, 'Unto God''s eternal sphere.'),
(223, 1, 1, 'Thou blessed Holy Spirit,'),
(223, 1, 2, 'Thy comfort is our stay;'),
(223, 1, 3, 'Throughout our pilgrim journey'),
(223, 1, 4, 'Thy help attends our way;'),
(223, 1, 5, 'And now, as thus assembled,'),
(223, 1, 6, 'Our souls with fervour glow;'),
(223, 1, 7, 'We would enjoy Thy service,'),
(223, 1, 8, 'Thy gracious presence know.'),
(223, 2, 1, 'Assured, we come with boldness'),
(223, 2, 2, 'Before the throne of grace,'),
(223, 2, 3, 'Knowing the One who serveth'),
(223, 2, 4, 'In that exalted place.'),
(223, 2, 5, 'Thus would our hearts in quietness'),
(223, 2, 6, 'Express their deep desires,'),
(223, 2, 7, 'And find in these sweet moments'),
(223, 2, 8, 'A strength that never tires.'),
(224, 1, 1, 'Though all the beasts on earth be slain'),
(224, 1, 2, 'To wash away sin''s crimson stain,'),
(224, 1, 3, 'Though all their blood should flow,'),
(224, 1, 4, 'The sacrifice would be in vain,'),
(224, 1, 5, 'Iniquity would still remain:'),
(224, 1, 6, 'Sin is not cancelled so.'),
(224, 2, 1, 'A better sacrifice than these'),
(224, 2, 2, 'It needs, the conscience to appease,'),
(224, 2, 3, 'Or satisfy the Lord;'),
(224, 2, 4, 'No blood hath virtue to atone'),
(224, 2, 5, 'For man''s offence, but His alone'),
(224, 2, 6, 'Whose title is the Word:'),
(224, 3, 1, 'His, who could say, Himself the Son,'),
(224, 3, 2, 'That with the Father He is one,'),
(224, 3, 3, 'Who made the world around:'),
(224, 3, 4, 'His, who Jehovah''s Fellow stood,'),
(224, 3, 5, 'And claimed equality with God,'),
(224, 3, 6, 'Whose glory knows no bound.'),
(224, 4, 1, 'Jesus the Christ, on earth His Name,'),
(224, 4, 2, 'He came - in love to sinners came -'),
(224, 4, 3, 'And bowed His head and died;'),
(224, 4, 4, 'A full atonement now is made,'),
(224, 4, 5, 'The ransom by Himself is paid,'),
(224, 4, 6, 'And justice satisfied.'),
(224, 5, 1, 'That sinners might draw near to Him,'),
(224, 5, 2, 'God planned this great, this gracious scheme,'),
(224, 5, 3, 'And found the ransom too.'),
(224, 5, 4, 'Let all His saints their voices raise,'),
(224, 5, 5, 'And sing the great Redeemer''s praise'),
(224, 5, 6, 'While endless ages flow.'),
(225, 1, 1, 'O scenes of heavenly joy!'),
(225, 1, 2, 'The Father''s house above;'),
(225, 1, 3, 'Where cloudless peace without alloy'),
(225, 1, 4, 'Fills all that home of love.'),
(225, 2, 1, 'The Father''s full delight'),
(225, 2, 2, 'Is centred in the Son;'),
(225, 2, 3, 'And countless tongues in heav''n unite'),
(225, 2, 4, 'To tell what He hath done.'),
(225, 3, 1, 'The Father made us meet'),
(225, 3, 2, 'With saints in light to dwell;'),
(225, 3, 3, 'And now we chant His praises sweet,'),
(225, 3, 4, 'Whose love we know so well.'),
(225, 4, 1, 'E''en now we taste the love,'),
(225, 4, 2, 'And know the mighty power,'),
(225, 4, 3, 'By which we''ll rise to realms above'),
(225, 4, 4, 'When waiting time is o''er.'),
(225, 5, 1, 'There glory bright and fair'),
(225, 5, 2, 'Shines with celestial beam;'),
(225, 5, 3, 'For He who suffered once is there,'),
(225, 5, 4, 'Its centre and its theme.'),
(225, 6, 1, 'The Lamb enthroned shall there'),
(225, 6, 2, 'Engage each raptured heart;'),
(225, 6, 3, 'While myriad saints Christ''s likeness bear,'),
(225, 6, 4, 'And have with Him their part.'),
(225, 7, 1, 'Praise Him again, again!'),
(225, 7, 2, 'For us the cross He bore;'),
(225, 7, 3, 'Now all is Yea, and all Amen,'),
(225, 7, 4, 'In Him for evermore.'),
(226, 1, 1, 'O glorious Lord! what thoughts Thy mind did fill,'),
(226, 1, 2, 'When from Thy God Thou cam''st to do His will!'),
(226, 1, 3, 'How deep, indeed, the joy that filled Thy heart -'),
(226, 1, 4, 'That myriad sons with Thee should find their part!'),
(226, 2, 1, 'Thy brethren, Lord, Thine own and one with Thee,'),
(226, 2, 2, 'Were in Thy heart - that they should with Thee be;'),
(226, 2, 3, 'Thy church complete and in Thy beauty dressed;'),
(226, 2, 4, 'The day of God, and love divine at rest.'),
(226, 3, 1, 'O blessed Lord, what treasured thoughts unfold'),
(226, 3, 2, 'In light divine, as we Thy face behold!'),
(226, 3, 3, 'Now on our view unbounded glories break,'),
(226, 3, 4, 'That speak Thy fame and songs eternal wake.'),
(227, 1, 1, 'Assembled here, O Lord,'),
(227, 1, 2, 'And gathered to Thy Name,'),
(227, 1, 3, 'We trace Thy path of love,'),
(227, 1, 4, 'Thy worthiness acclaim -'),
(227, 1, 5, 'Thou who in love couldst stoop so low;'),
(227, 1, 6, 'Till Thou dost come Thy death we show.'),
(227, 2, 1, 'Our hearts are moved, blest Lord,'),
(227, 2, 2, 'As occupied with Thee;'),
(227, 2, 3, 'We hear afresh Thy word,'),
(227, 2, 4, 'This do, remember Me.'),
(227, 2, 5, 'With one accord, as thus set free,'),
(227, 2, 6, 'We gladly now respond to Thee.'),
(228, 1, 1, 'All through this desert dry'),
(228, 1, 2, 'My path His footsteps trace,'),
(228, 1, 3, 'And He doth all my need supply'),
(228, 1, 4, 'In this sad, empty place.'),
(228, 1, 5, 'Up to the father there'),
(228, 1, 6, 'Doth He attract my heart -'),
(228, 1, 7, 'Doth make this earth a desert drear,'),
(228, 1, 8, 'And make me quite apart.'),
(228, 2, 1, 'In Christ I find repose,'),
(228, 2, 2, 'Nor follow Him in vain;'),
(228, 2, 3, 'My soul no loss nor sorrow knows'),
(228, 2, 4, 'When He Himself''s my gain.'),
(228, 2, 5, 'Though long and hard the road,'),
(228, 2, 6, 'Faith''s eyes are on the goal;'),
(228, 2, 7, 'He uses trials for my good,');
INSERT INTO `hymn_line` (`hymn_no`, `vers_no`, `line_no`, `line_text`) VALUES (228, 2, 8, 'And thus preserves my soul.'),
(228, 3, 1, 'Thus joyful, bright and free,'),
(228, 3, 2, 'I take the heav''nly road;'),
(228, 3, 3, 'My soul vibrates with melody,'),
(228, 3, 4, 'My song is ever - God!'),
(228, 3, 5, 'To Thee I have recourse'),
(228, 3, 6, 'When sorrow fills my soul;'),
(228, 3, 7, 'Thy staff and rod are my resource,'),
(228, 3, 8, 'To comfort and console.'),
(228, 4, 1, 'O what amazing grace'),
(228, 4, 2, 'To know Thee here below!'),
(228, 4, 3, 'To this great end Thy steps I trace,'),
(228, 4, 4, 'And onward, upward go.'),
(228, 4, 5, 'Thy face I soon shall see,'),
(228, 4, 6, 'O mighty Saviour, there;'),
(228, 4, 7, 'I have in Thee full victory,'),
(228, 4, 8, 'And shall Thy glory share.'),
(229, 1, 1, 'Thy Name must live, whatever names may die;'),
(229, 1, 2, 'It must fill all the earth, as heav''n on high.'),
(229, 1, 3, 'Jesus! Thy Name by all shall yet be known,'),
(229, 1, 4, 'All kings and nations shall Thy greatness own.'),
(229, 2, 1, 'Thou livest, Saviour, and all grace is there,'),
(229, 2, 2, 'That with such beauty shone in Thee down here;'),
(229, 2, 3, 'No trait is lost, each beauteous grace we see,'),
(229, 2, 4, 'All brought through death to shine eternally.'),
(229, 3, 1, 'Our joy is full - we have Thee, Jesus, still;'),
(229, 3, 2, 'The glory bright Thy precious Name doth fill;'),
(229, 3, 3, 'What holds Thy people now while here on earth'),
(229, 3, 4, 'Is what Thou art in all Thy wondrous worth.'),
(230, 1, 1, 'O Lord, when we the path retrace'),
(230, 1, 2, 'Which Thou on earth hast trod,'),
(230, 1, 3, 'To man Thy wondrous love and grace,'),
(230, 1, 4, 'Thy faithfulness to God:-'),
(230, 2, 1, 'Faithful amidst unfaithfulness,'),
(230, 2, 2, '''Mid darkness only light,'),
(230, 2, 3, 'Thou didst Thy Father''s name confess,'),
(230, 2, 4, 'And in His will delight;'),
(230, 3, 1, 'Unmoved by Satan''s subtle wiles,'),
(230, 3, 2, 'Or Suff''ring, shame and loss,'),
(230, 3, 3, 'Thy path, uncheered by earthly smiles,'),
(230, 3, 4, 'Led only to the cross;'),
(230, 4, 1, 'Thy love, by man so sorely tried,'),
(230, 4, 2, 'Proved stronger than the grave;'),
(230, 4, 3, 'Though man in hatred pierced Thy side,'),
(230, 4, 4, 'Thy blood love''s answer gave:-'),
(230, 5, 1, 'We wonder at Thy lowly mind,'),
(230, 5, 2, 'And fain would like Thee be,'),
(230, 5, 3, 'And all our rest and pleasure find'),
(230, 5, 4, 'In learning, Lord, from Thee.'),
(231, 1, 1, 'Father, to Thy gracious throne'),
(231, 1, 2, 'We draw nigh in all our need,'),
(231, 1, 3, 'In the Name of Him alone'),
(231, 1, 4, 'Who for us in heav''n doth plead.'),
(231, 2, 1, 'May Thy holy Name be praised'),
(231, 2, 2, 'Now on earth as ''tis in heav''n;'),
(231, 2, 3, 'May Thy glory high be raised,'),
(231, 2, 4, 'Unto Thee be worship giv''n.'),
(231, 3, 1, 'Here on earth beset by foes,'),
(231, 3, 2, 'Well beloved by Christ her Head,'),
(231, 3, 3, 'May the church in love''s repose.'),
(231, 3, 4, 'Her appointed journey tread.'),
(231, 4, 1, 'May the Christ dwell in our heart,'),
(231, 4, 2, 'Known in love past human ken:'),
(231, 4, 3, 'Joying in our heav''nly part,'),
(231, 4, 4, 'Counsel deep and vast for men.'),
(231, 5, 1, 'May we here our strength renew,'),
(231, 5, 2, 'Mount with eagle''s wings above,'),
(231, 5, 3, 'Run the race with Him in view,'),
(231, 5, 4, 'Faint not here, but walk in love.'),
(232, 1, 1, 'Lord Jesus Christ, our voices rise as one'),
(232, 1, 2, 'And tribute raise.'),
(232, 1, 3, 'Amongst Thine own we would exalt Thy Name,'),
(232, 1, 4, 'And sing Thy praise.'),
(232, 1, 5, 'To Thee, O King of kings and Lord of lords,'),
(232, 1, 6, 'Our song would be. Thy glories strike the chords.'),
(232, 2, 1, 'The morning stars together once did raise,'),
(232, 2, 2, 'In joyful throng,'),
(232, 2, 3, 'Their glorious lays, as later Israel''s praise'),
(232, 2, 4, 'In psalm and song.'),
(232, 2, 5, 'Creation and redemption''s glory known,'),
(232, 2, 6, 'Celestial hosts break forth around the throne'),
(232, 3, 1, 'Worthy art Thou! We join the great refrain;'),
(232, 3, 2, 'Chief place Thou hast,'),
(232, 3, 3, 'O Root of David Thou, the Lamb once slain,'),
(232, 3, 4, 'The First and Last!'),
(232, 3, 5, 'To Him who is, who was and is to come,'),
(232, 3, 6, 'Be glory now as we extol Thy fame!'),
(233, 1, 1, 'Ours is a pardon bought with blood,'),
(233, 1, 2, 'Amazing truth! the blood of One'),
(233, 1, 3, 'Who, without usurpation, could'),
(233, 1, 4, 'Lay claim to heav''n''s eternal throne!'),
(233, 2, 1, 'No victim of inferior worth'),
(233, 2, 2, 'Could bear the stroke that justice aimed;'),
(233, 2, 3, 'For none but He, in heav''n or earth,'),
(233, 2, 4, 'Could offer that which justice claimed.'),
(233, 3, 1, 'But He, the Lord of glory, came;'),
(233, 3, 2, 'Upon the cross He bowed His head;'),
(233, 3, 3, 'He suffered pain, He suffered shame,'),
(233, 3, 4, 'And lay a prisoner with the dead.'),
(233, 4, 1, 'But lo! He''s risen from the grave,'),
(233, 4, 2, 'And bears the greatest, noblest Name:'),
(233, 4, 3, 'The Lord - almighty now to save'),
(233, 4, 4, 'From sin, from death, from endless shame.'),
(234, 1, 1, 'O Lord, we joy that Thou art glory-crowned,'),
(234, 1, 2, 'Who by Thy death to God hast brought us nigh;'),
(234, 1, 3, 'In Thee alone is our forgiveness found,'),
(234, 1, 4, 'And everlasting praises rise on high.'),
(234, 2, 1, 'We praise Thee, for Thou didst in death lay down'),
(234, 2, 2, 'Thy precious life, an off''ring once for all;'),
(234, 2, 3, 'For ever cleansed by blood, our joy and crown'),
(234, 2, 4, 'We owe to Thee, and thus before Thee fall.'),
(234, 3, 1, 'We bless Thee, glorious Lord; Thou risen art;'),
(234, 3, 2, 'And we, set free from sin and death, rejoice'),
(234, 3, 3, 'To know in Thee, in life, our endless part,'),
(234, 3, 4, 'As with adoring thoughts our praise we voice.'),
(234, 4, 1, 'Soon Thou art coming, Lord; we wait for Thee!'),
(234, 4, 2, 'Soon all Thine own shall meet Thee in the air,'),
(234, 4, 3, 'And we shall dwell with Thee eternally,'),
(234, 4, 4, 'All changed, and like to Thee, Thy place to share.'),
(235, 1, 1, 'We''ll praise Thee, glorious Lord,'),
(235, 1, 2, 'Who died to set us free;'),
(235, 1, 3, 'No earthly songs can joy afford'),
(235, 1, 4, 'Like heav''nly melody.'),
(235, 2, 1, 'Love that no suff''ring stayed'),
(235, 2, 2, 'We''ll praise - true love divine;'),
(235, 2, 3, 'Love that for us atonement made,'),
(235, 2, 4, 'Love that has made us Thine.'),
(235, 3, 1, 'Love in Thy lonely life'),
(235, 3, 2, 'Of sorrow here below;'),
(235, 3, 3, 'Thy words of grace, with mercy rife,'),
(235, 3, 4, 'Make grateful praises flow.'),
(235, 4, 1, 'Love, that on death''s dark vale'),
(235, 4, 2, 'Its sweetest odours spread,'),
(235, 4, 3, 'Where sin o''er all seemed to prevail,'),
(235, 4, 4, 'Redemption''s glory shed.'),
(235, 5, 1, 'And now we see Thee ris''n,'),
(235, 5, 2, 'Who once for us hast died,'),
(235, 5, 3, 'Seated above the highest heav''n:'),
(235, 5, 4, 'The Father''s Glorified.'),
(235, 6, 1, 'Soon wilt Thou take Thy throne,'),
(235, 6, 2, 'Thy foes Thy footstool made,'),
(235, 6, 3, 'And bring us with Thee as Thine own,'),
(235, 6, 4, 'In glory love displayed.'),
(235, 7, 1, 'Jesus, we wait for Thee,'),
(235, 7, 2, 'With Thee to have our part;'),
(235, 7, 3, 'What can full joy and blessing be'),
(235, 7, 4, 'But being where Thou art!'),
(236, 1, 1, 'O Jesus, Lord, we long'),
(236, 1, 2, 'Thy face to see,'),
(236, 1, 3, 'To be for evermore'),
(236, 1, 4, 'At home with Thee.'),
(236, 2, 1, 'No more to grieve Thy heart'),
(236, 2, 2, 'By failure sore,'),
(236, 2, 3, 'But join Thee where Thou art,'),
(236, 2, 4, 'The journey o''er.'),
(236, 3, 1, 'O Lord, what joy will fill'),
(236, 3, 2, 'Thy heart of love'),
(236, 3, 3, 'To have Thine own with Thee'),
(236, 3, 4, 'In heav''n above!'),
(236, 4, 1, 'To loose the bands of death,'),
(236, 4, 2, 'And thence set free'),
(236, 4, 3, 'The bodies of Thine own,'),
(236, 4, 4, 'Redeemed by Thee!'),
(236, 5, 1, 'To see Thy bride at last'),
(236, 5, 2, 'In Thee complete,'),
(236, 5, 3, 'Of Thy soul''s travail deep,'),
(236, 5, 4, 'Fruition sweet!'),
(236, 6, 1, 'Thy kin is she, O Lord,'),
(236, 6, 2, 'And one with Thee,'),
(236, 6, 3, 'To be for Thy delight'),
(236, 6, 4, 'Eternally.'),
(236, 7, 1, 'Rejoicing in Thy joy,'),
(236, 7, 2, 'With one accord'),
(236, 7, 3, 'Spirit and bride say, "Come!"'),
(236, 7, 4, 'O Jesus, Lord!'),
(237, 1, 1, 'Father, we celebrate Thy praise.'),
(237, 1, 2, 'Adoringly we bless'),
(237, 1, 3, 'With glad acclaim Thy holy Name,'),
(237, 1, 4, 'Revealed in righteousness.'),
(237, 2, 1, 'Where every whit Thy glory tells'),
(237, 2, 2, 'Within the temple''s shrine,'),
(237, 2, 3, 'As sons we raise our hymn of praise'),
(237, 2, 4, 'And joy in love divine.'),
(237, 3, 1, 'The voice of Christ is heard o''er all'),
(237, 3, 2, 'In accents sweet and clear;'),
(237, 3, 3, 'Thy Name is shared as now declared'),
(237, 3, 4, 'Unto His brethren here.'),
(237, 4, 1, 'As is Thy Name so is Thy praise;'),
(237, 4, 2, '(Our voices rise as one) -'),
(237, 4, 3, 'Father, to Thee all glory be'),
(237, 4, 4, 'Through Thy beloved Son!'),
(238, 1, 1, 'When peace like a river attendeth my way,'),
(238, 1, 2, 'When sorrows like sea-billows roll,'),
(238, 1, 3, 'Whatever my lot, Thou hast taught me to say,'),
(238, 1, 4, 'It is well, it is well with my soul.'),
(238, 2, 1, 'Though Satan should buffet, though trials should come,'),
(238, 2, 2, 'Let this blest assurance control,'),
(238, 2, 3, 'That Christ hath regarded my helpless estate,'),
(238, 2, 4, 'And hath shed His own blood for my soul.'),
(238, 3, 1, 'My sins - O the bliss of this glorious thought -'),
(238, 3, 2, 'My sins - not in part but the whole -'),
(238, 3, 3, 'Were borne on the cross, and are gone evermore.'),
(238, 3, 4, 'Praise the Lord, praise the Lord, O my soul!'),
(238, 4, 1, 'O Lord, ''tis for Thee, for Thy coming we wait,'),
(238, 4, 2, 'The sky, not the grave, is our goal.'),
(238, 4, 3, 'O voice of archangel! O trumpet of God!'),
(238, 4, 4, 'Blessed hope! blessed rest of my soul!'),
(239, 1, 1, 'Christ did for sins atone,'),
(239, 1, 2, 'And on the cross He bled;'),
(239, 1, 3, 'Forgiveness may be known,'),
(239, 1, 4, 'Because His blood was shed'),
(239, 1, 5, 'To free Thee from the bonds of sin,'),
(239, 1, 6, 'And give Thee peace and joy within.'),
(239, 2, 1, 'His face He firmly set,'),
(239, 2, 2, 'And all the road He trod,'),
(239, 2, 3, 'Till justice had been met'),
(239, 2, 4, 'Before a holy God,'),
(239, 2, 5, 'Who now is free, at such a cost,'),
(239, 2, 6, 'To offer mercy to the lost.'),
(239, 3, 1, 'But O, His suff''rings o''er,'),
(239, 3, 2, 'He lives in glory there;'),
(239, 3, 3, 'Alive to die no more,'),
(239, 3, 4, 'He waits with us to share'),
(239, 3, 5, 'His Father''s house - that home so bright -'),
(239, 3, 6, 'Th''eternal day without a night.'),
