(283, 2, 4, 'We raise our song to Thee - our blest employ!'),
(283, 3, 1, 'We praise Thee, blessed Lord; our souls would move'),
(283, 3, 2, 'With joy to answer to Thy precious love.');
INSERT INTO `hymn_line` (`hymn_no`, `vers_no`, `line_no`, `line_text`) VALUES (283, 3, 3, 'We taste of heav''nly joys with Thee - how blest!'),
(283, 3, 4, 'Thine own heart satisfied, and ours at rest.'),
(284, 1, 1, '"Not of the world" - blest words of Christ the Lord'),
(284, 1, 2, 'To those who here attended on His word!'),
(284, 1, 3, 'They call to us, amid our pilgrim ways,'),
(284, 1, 4, 'And draw us, Father, to Thy world of praise.'),
(284, 2, 1, 'Out of the world to Thine own blest abode'),
(284, 2, 2, 'We follow our Forerunner to His God.'),
(284, 2, 3, 'As, bought by blood, we do not here belong -'),
(284, 2, 4, '"Not of the world" becomes our joyful song.'),
(284, 3, 1, '"Not of the world", O words of deep delight!'),
(284, 3, 2, 'What rest and strength their heav''nly tones incite!'),
(284, 3, 3, 'Strangers below and citizens above,'),
(284, 3, 4, 'May we be worthy, Father, of such love!'),
(284, 4, 1, 'O teach us all, who have this glorious lot,'),
(284, 4, 2, 'To seek for nothing where our Lord is not.'),
(284, 4, 3, 'Be this our song, our glory and our plea:'),
(284, 4, 4, '"Not of the world" - our springs are all in Thee.'),
(285, 1, 1, 'Blest Spirit, now we worship Thee;'),
(285, 1, 2, 'Thou art in us the power'),
(285, 1, 3, 'To know Christ''s love and serve Him thus,'),
(285, 1, 4, 'Responsive in this hour.'),
(285, 2, 1, 'And Thou art God, Thou Holy One;'),
(285, 2, 2, 'Unseen and yet well known,'),
(285, 2, 3, 'Thou art Thyself the bond between'),
(285, 2, 4, 'Christ Jesus and His own;'),
(285, 3, 1, 'More blessed still, the bond between'),
(285, 3, 2, 'The Father and the Son;'),
(285, 3, 3, 'Co-equal, Thou, in deity,'),
(285, 3, 4, 'With Them for ever One.'),
(285, 4, 1, 'We sing to thee adoringly,'),
(285, 4, 2, 'With reverential joy;'),
(285, 4, 3, 'In praises rendered unto Thee'),
(285, 4, 4, 'We would our lips employ.'),
(286, 1, 1, 'What rich eternal bursts of praise'),
(286, 1, 2, 'Shall fill yon courts through endless days,'),
(286, 1, 3, 'When time shall cease to be!'),
(286, 1, 4, 'Round and around the notes shall swell,'),
(286, 1, 5, 'As each redeemed one joins to tell'),
(286, 1, 6, 'Thy love, so vast and free.'),
(286, 2, 1, 'Each shall the Saviour''s likeness bear,'),
(286, 2, 2, 'A royal crown each brow shall wear,'),
(286, 2, 3, 'And robes unsullied white.'),
(286, 2, 4, 'The everlasting song shall be'),
(286, 2, 5, 'To Thee, O Lamb of God, to thee,'),
(286, 2, 6, '''Mid scenes of purest light.'),
(286, 3, 1, 'Our joy unhindered then with Thee,'),
(286, 3, 2, 'Our eyes undimmed Thy glory see,'),
(286, 3, 3, 'Whilst worthy praise we give.'),
(286, 3, 4, 'As we await that cloudless day,'),
(286, 3, 5, 'Our burning hearts with rapture say'),
(286, 3, 6, 'He died that we might live!'),
(287, 1, 1, 'Jesus! life-giving sound,'),
(287, 1, 2, 'The joy of earth and heav''n;'),
(287, 1, 3, 'No other help is found,'),
(287, 1, 4, 'No other name is giv''n'),
(287, 1, 5, 'In which the sons of men can boast,'),
(287, 1, 6, 'Than His who seeks and saves the lost.'),
(287, 2, 1, 'His Name the sinner hears'),
(287, 2, 2, 'And is from guilt set free;'),
(287, 2, 3, '''Tis music in his ears,'),
(287, 2, 4, '''Tis life and victory;'),
(287, 2, 5, 'His heart o''erflows with sacred joy,'),
(287, 2, 6, 'And songs of praise his lips employ.'),
(287, 3, 1, 'Jesus! all praise above;'),
(287, 3, 2, 'We sing Thy blessed Name,'),
(287, 3, 3, 'We sing Thy dying love,'),
(287, 3, 4, 'Thy rising power proclaim:'),
(287, 3, 5, 'But soon, to give Thee worthy praise,'),
(287, 3, 6, 'Both heav''n and earth their songs shall raise.'),
(288, 1, 1, 'Our hearts Thou dost console, O Lord,'),
(288, 1, 2, 'Thou who affordest heav''nly light;'),
(288, 1, 3, 'Thy Spirit speaks to us Thy word,'),
(288, 1, 4, 'And dwells with us throughout the night.'),
(288, 2, 1, 'Thy voice, O Lord, is near at hand;'),
(288, 2, 2, 'The Spirit gives us access free;'),
(288, 2, 3, 'He helps us here to understand,'),
(288, 2, 4, 'And moves our hearts with thoughts of Thee.'),
(288, 3, 1, 'The memory of Thy wondrous love'),
(288, 3, 2, 'Thine own still treasure here below;'),
(288, 3, 3, 'While in this waste, from heav''n above'),
(288, 3, 4, 'Thy glory and Thy grace we know.'),
(288, 4, 1, 'Thine is the world of life, where more'),
(288, 4, 2, 'By far than Eshcol''s grapes is found:'),
(288, 4, 3, 'Refreshment, strength, from Thy vast store'),
(288, 4, 4, 'We have, despite the barren ground.'),
(288, 5, 1, 'But soon the Spirit''s gentle grace'),
(288, 5, 2, 'In service shall completed be;'),
(288, 5, 3, 'And we in light, and face to face -'),
(288, 5, 4, 'Thou Holy One - shall speak to Thee.'),
(289, 1, 1, 'Lord Jesus, holy lamb of God,'),
(289, 1, 2, 'Who shed''st for us Thine own life-blood,'),
(289, 1, 3, 'Come, teach us all Thy love - then pain'),
(289, 1, 4, 'In life were sweet, and death were gain.'),
(289, 2, 1, 'Take Thou our hearts, and let them be'),
(289, 2, 2, 'For ever held, O Lord, for Thee.'),
(289, 2, 3, 'Thy willing servants, let us wear'),
(289, 2, 4, 'The seal of love for ever there.'),
(289, 3, 1, 'How blest are they who still abide'),
(289, 3, 2, 'Close sheltered by Thy watchful side,'),
(289, 3, 3, 'Who life and strength from Thee receive,'),
(289, 3, 4, 'And with Thee move, and in Thee live!'),
(289, 4, 1, 'Ah, Lord, enlarge our scanty thought,'),
(289, 4, 2, 'To know the wonders Thou hast wrought;'),
(289, 4, 3, 'Unloose our stamm''ring tongues to tell'),
(289, 4, 4, 'Thy love, immense, unsearchable!'),
(290, 1, 1, 'I love to sing of Jesus,'),
(290, 1, 2, 'The story all so true,'),
(290, 1, 3, 'To me most sweet and precious,'),
(290, 1, 4, 'The old but ever new.'),
(290, 1, 5, 'He came from brightest glory,'),
(290, 1, 6, 'From radiant courts on high;'),
(290, 1, 7, 'How matchless is the story'),
(290, 1, 8, 'Of Him who came to die!'),
(290, 2, 1, '''Twas then my Saviour suffered,'),
(290, 2, 2, 'And tasted death for me;'),
(290, 2, 3, 'Yes, then the work He finished,'),
(290, 2, 4, 'That sets me ever free -'),
(290, 2, 5, 'My sins all laid upon Him,'),
(290, 2, 6, 'The wrath and judgment borne,'),
(290, 2, 7, 'The power of Satan broken,'),
(290, 2, 8, 'In Jesus'' death of scorn.'),
(290, 3, 1, 'And now the Lord is risen,'),
(290, 3, 2, 'His pain and travail o''er;'),
(290, 3, 3, 'Seated in highest heaven'),
(290, 3, 4, 'Alive, to die no more.'),
(290, 3, 5, 'And by the Holy Spirit'),
(290, 3, 6, 'He gives me, here below,'),
(290, 3, 7, 'Rich blessings to inherit,'),
(290, 3, 8, 'The love of God to know.'),
(290, 4, 1, '''Tis life and wondrous favour'),
(290, 4, 2, 'To live e''en now to God'),
(290, 4, 3, 'Through Him, the glorious Saviour'),
(290, 4, 4, 'Who shed His precious blood;'),
(290, 4, 5, 'And soon He''s coming for me,'),
(290, 4, 6, 'To take me home above,'),
(290, 4, 7, 'Where still I''ll sing the story'),
(290, 4, 8, 'Of Jesus and His love.'),
(291, 1, 1, 'Lo! He comes, from heav''n descending,'),
(291, 1, 2, 'Once for guilty sinners slain;'),
(291, 1, 3, 'Thousand thousand saints attending'),
(291, 1, 4, 'Swell the triumph of His train.'),
(291, 1, 5, 'Hallelujah!'),
(291, 1, 6, 'Jesus comes, and comes to reign.'),
(291, 2, 1, 'See the Saviour, long expected,'),
(291, 2, 2, 'Now in solemn pomp appear!'),
(291, 2, 3, 'And His saints, by man rejected,'),
(291, 2, 4, 'In His heav''nly glory share.'),
(291, 2, 5, 'Hallelujah!'),
(291, 2, 6, 'See the Son of God appear!'),
(291, 3, 1, 'Israel''s race shall then behold Him,'),
(291, 3, 2, 'Full of grace and majesty;'),
(291, 3, 3, 'Though they set at nought and sold Him,'),
(291, 3, 4, 'Pierced and nailed Him to the tree,'),
