(293, 2, 4, 'In Thee accepted by the Father''s grace.'),
(293, 3, 1, 'Thy beauties, Lord, Thy holy precious worth,'),
(293, 3, 2, 'Surpassing far the deepest joys of earth,'),
(293, 3, 3, 'Attract our hearts - our joy Thy constant love,'),
(293, 3, 4, 'Thyself our object in those scenes above.'),
(293, 4, 1, 'Thy fulness, Lord, of light and love divine,'),
