(294, 3, 1, 'Thou dost fill all in this blest sphere'),
(294, 3, 2, 'Where we are at Thy side;'),
(294, 3, 3, 'With Thee, Thy fulness, brought so near,'),
(294, 3, 4, 'Thy body and Thy bride.'),
(294, 4, 1, 'And O how blest! that place above'),
(294, 4, 2, 'Th''assembly shares with Thee,'),
(294, 4, 3, 'As purposed in the Father''s love'),
(294, 4, 4, 'His joy and Thine to be.'),
(295, 1, 1, 'Unto Thee, blest Holy Spirit,'),
(295, 1, 2, 'Now we offer praise,'),
