(300, 2, 4, 'To work out all His great designs in man.'),
(300, 3, 1, 'And when at length the Son on earth did stand,'),
(300, 3, 2, 'Thou didst descend in love to mark Him out;'),
(300, 3, 3, 'Thenceforth to be the power of His hand,'),
(300, 3, 4, 'E''en to the off''ring of Himself to God.'),
(300, 4, 1, 'And now in lowlier stoop and tireless love,'),
