(329, 4, 3, 'The glories of the living God,'),
(329, 4, 4, 'The riches of His grace!'),
(330, 1, 1, 'Father, from our hearts is springing,'),
(330, 1, 2, 'By the Holy Spirit''s power,'),
(330, 1, 3, 'Praise which He, the Son, is leading'),
(330, 1, 4, 'To Thyself in this blest hour.'),
(330, 2, 1, 'What a joy to call Thee Father,'),
(330, 2, 2, 'Blest indeed as with Thy Son,'),
(330, 2, 3, 'And to know Thy love in nearness,'),
(330, 2, 4, 'Fruit of triumphs He has won.'),
(330, 3, 1, 'Great the cost to Thee, blest Father,'),
(330, 3, 2, 'For Thou didst not spare Thy Son,'),
(330, 3, 3, 'Answered now in those who worship'),
(330, 3, 4, 'In the good of what He''s done.'),
(330, 4, 1, 'So to Thee, supreme in all things,'),
(330, 4, 2, 'Over all, the Father blest,'),
(330, 4, 3, 'Worship, joy and adoration,'),
(330, 4, 4, 'As we greet Thee in Thy rest.'),
(331, 1, 1, 'It is to Thee our voices now we raise,'),
(331, 1, 2, 'Blest Spirit of adoption; Thee we praise,'),
(331, 1, 3, 'As, in the light of sonship''s glorious place,'),
(331, 1, 4, 'We serve by Thee before the Father''s face.'),
(331, 2, 1, 'Thy blessed, holy Person be adored'),
(331, 2, 2, 'By those whose hearts respond with one accord;'),
(331, 2, 3, 'For Thou hast served that we, through boundless grace,'),
(331, 2, 4, 'Might know with Christ a son''s eternal place.'),
(331, 3, 1, 'Access by Thee, through Christ, in that blest sphere -'),
(331, 3, 2, 'We know and prove the love which casts out fear;'),
(331, 3, 3, 'And, restful in God''s grace as now brought nigh,'),
(331, 3, 4, 'We joy with Thee, and "Abba, Father!" cry.'),
(332, 1, 1, 'Hark to the message sounding'),
(332, 1, 2, 'Out from the throne above,'),
(332, 1, 3, 'Telling of grace abounding,'),
(332, 1, 4, 'Telling of perfect love.'),
(332, 1, 5, 'Hark to the wondrous story,'),
(332, 1, 6, 'Redemption''s price is paid;'),
(332, 1, 7, 'Jesus is crowned with glory,'),
(332, 1, 8, 'Both Lord and Christ is made.'),
(332, 2, 1, 'None other name is given,'),
(332, 2, 2, 'Jesus alone can save;'),
(332, 2, 3, 'In love He came from heaven,'),
(332, 2, 4, 'Himself a ransom gave.'),
(332, 2, 5, 'In Him was grace abounding,'),
(332, 2, 6, 'He paid in full the price;'),
(332, 2, 7, 'O love immense, astounding,'),
(332, 2, 8, 'O wondrous sacrifice!'),
(332, 3, 1, 'The Spirit now bears witness'),
(332, 3, 2, 'To Christ enthroned on high:'),
(332, 3, 3, 'Redemption''s work accomplished'),
(332, 3, 4, 'By Him who came to die.'),
(332, 3, 5, 'And now, in accents tender,'),
(332, 3, 6, 'The Saviour speaks today;'),
(332, 3, 7, 'Be wise, to Him surrender;'),
(332, 3, 8, 'His gracious call obey!'),
(333, 1, 1, 'Our God and Father, we are here to share'),
(333, 1, 2, 'Interests divine;'),
(333, 1, 3, 'True is our love and genuine our care'),
(333, 1, 4, 'For what is Thine,'),
(333, 1, 5, 'As moved by Christ''s own feelings in our heart,'),
(333, 1, 6, 'We long to bear with priestly hands our part.'),
(333, 2, 1, 'The sanctity of Thine abode on earth'),
(333, 2, 2, 'Our hearts would guard,'),
(333, 2, 3, 'That by unholy ways its holy worth'),
(333, 2, 4, 'May not be marred.'),
(333, 2, 5, 'The couch of Solomon we would surround'),
(333, 2, 6, 'With valiant love and reverence profound.'),
(333, 3, 1, 'Blest Spirit, who art here in charge of all'),
(333, 3, 2, 'God''s interests great,'),
(333, 3, 3, 'On Thee, our Paraclete, we humbly call'),
(333, 3, 4, 'As here we wait.'),
(333, 3, 5, 'Hold us in faith, in dignity and power,'),
(333, 3, 6, 'Throughout this privileged and sacred hour.'),
(334, 1, 1, 'In light unclouded dwells the mighty God,'),
(334, 1, 2, 'His glory all creation doth proclaim;'),
(334, 1, 3, 'A Spirit - love and light, the Holy One -'),
(334, 1, 4, 'Who is, who was, who is to come, the Same!'),
(334, 2, 1, 'The only glorious, the eternal God,'),
(334, 2, 2, 'Who ever lived before beginnings were!'),
(334, 2, 3, 'All heaven''s constellations pale before'),
(334, 2, 4, 'The glory of the One who set them there!'),
(334, 3, 1, 'The Triune God, almighty, yet unseen;'),
(334, 3, 2, 'The ever holy, holy, holy One'),
(334, 3, 3, 'Whose word existence to creation gave,'),
(334, 3, 4, 'When dwelling in eternity alone!'),
(334, 4, 1, 'What joy it is to contemplate Thyself'),
(334, 4, 2, 'In Christ revealed, the everlasting God!'),
(334, 4, 3, 'To learn Thy wisdom, search Thy matchless grace;'),
(334, 4, 4, 'To worship Thee, as saints redeemed by blood!'),
(334, 5, 1, 'To see Thy glory in the face of Christ,'),
(334, 5, 2, 'And without let enjoy - in heav''n above,'),
(334, 5, 3, 'In realms of cloudless light and joy and peace -'),
(334, 5, 4, 'Thine own unending, changeless, perfect love!'),
(335, 1, 1, 'Lord, Thy ways are past our searching,'),
(335, 1, 2, 'Infinite Thy holy mind!'),
(335, 1, 3, 'Thou dost break earth''s links asunder,'),
(335, 1, 4, 'To Thyself our souls dost bind.'),
(335, 2, 1, 'By the cords of love Thou drawest'),
(335, 2, 2, 'Each blest object of Thy grace;'),
(335, 2, 3, 'Thou wilt daily keep us near Thee,'),
(335, 2, 4, 'Till in heav''n we see Thy face.'),
(335, 3, 1, 'Many foes surround our footsteps;'),
(335, 3, 2, 'None shall mar our joy in Thee!'),
(335, 3, 3, 'Soon will change earth''s toil and sorrow'),
(335, 3, 4, 'For a bright eternity.'),
(335, 4, 1, 'We would trust Thee without seeing,'),
(335, 4, 2, 'Knowing that Thy way is best;'),
(335, 4, 3, 'Dark or bright, in Thee confiding,'),
(335, 4, 4, 'Shall our hearts find peace and rest.'),
(336, 1, 1, 'Blest God and Father, source of joy'),
(336, 1, 2, 'For all Thine own in sonship''s place,'),
(336, 1, 3, 'Our songs of praise arise to Thee -'),
(336, 1, 4, 'We worship now before Thy face.'),
(336, 2, 1, 'Thy Spirit doth our hearts sustain,'),
(336, 2, 2, 'As we through Christ are near to Thee;'),
(336, 2, 3, 'Thy holy love fills every heart,'),
(336, 2, 4, 'And in Thy presence blest are we.'),
(336, 3, 1, 'Thou in Thy wondrous love hast planned'),
(336, 3, 2, 'That we with Christ should have our part,'),
(336, 3, 3, 'And share that home of glory bright'),
(336, 3, 4, 'With Him who fills with joy Thy heart.'),
(336, 4, 1, 'O blessed home, where Thou dost dwell'),
(336, 4, 2, 'In holy love and glory bright!'),
(336, 4, 3, 'Near Thee, Thy love rests on us now,'),
(336, 4, 4, 'And we in Christ are Thy delight.'),
(336, 5, 1, 'Blest in Thy presence - glorious place -'),
(336, 5, 2, 'With joy we hymn Thyself on high.'),
(336, 5, 3, 'O God of love, our song we raise,'),
(336, 5, 4, 'And "Father" by the Spirit cry.'),
(337, 1, 1, 'Blest Holy Spirit, Comforter -'),
(337, 1, 2, 'Though here in mystery -'),
(337, 1, 3, 'Thy lowly service does not hide'),
(337, 1, 4, 'Thy place in Deity:'),
(337, 2, 1, 'Thy Person all inscrutable -'),
(337, 2, 2, 'Yet pleased with us to be -'),
(337, 2, 3, 'Thy presence infinitely blest!'),
(337, 2, 4, 'As God we worship Thee.'),
(338, 1, 1, 'The Lord is coming; lift your heads!'),
(338, 1, 2, 'Ye ransomed saints, rejoice!'),
(338, 1, 3, 'Soon shall we meet Him in the air,'),
(338, 1, 4, 'And answer to His voice.'),
(338, 2, 1, 'The Lord is coming; faith gives place'),
(338, 2, 2, 'To actuality,'),
(338, 2, 3, 'This mortal swallowed up by life'),
(338, 2, 4, 'In immortality.'),
(338, 3, 1, 'The Lord is coming; what delight'),
(338, 3, 2, 'Our hearts anticipate!'),
(338, 3, 3, 'The glory of that blessed sight'),
(338, 3, 4, 'We eagerly await.'),
(338, 4, 1, 'Yea, Lord, Thou comest - hope how blest!'),
(338, 4, 2, 'Thy call we soon shall hear;'),
(338, 4, 3, 'And then in glory shall Thy bride'),
(338, 4, 4, 'With Thee, the King, appear.'),
(339, 1, 1, 'Lord, in Thy supper now we see'),
(339, 1, 2, 'The tokens of Thy matchless love!'),
(339, 1, 3, 'Not death itself could stronger be'),
(339, 1, 4, 'Than those affections Thou didst prove.'),
(339, 1, 5, 'Thy peace, Thy joy Thou bringest here'),
(339, 1, 6, 'Our souls to bless, our hearts to cheer.'),
(339, 2, 1, 'The bread and cup before us now'),
(339, 2, 2, 'Are witness to a work complete,'),
(339, 2, 3, 'Through darkness dread, O Lord, when Thou'),
(339, 2, 4, 'The awful power of death didst meet!'),
(339, 2, 5, 'We praise Thee, Lord, as now come nigh,'),
(339, 2, 6, 'Thee - whom we soon shall praise on high!'),
(340, 1, 1, 'Eternal King of those who reign,'),
(340, 1, 2, 'To Thee be honour, might, Amen.'),
(340, 1, 3, 'Thou, God from all eternity,'),
(340, 1, 4, 'Alone hast immortality.'),
(340, 1, 5, 'Thy dwelling light, Thy form unknown,'),
(340, 1, 6, 'Supreme art Thou, O God, alone!'),
(340, 2, 1, 'The only wise, invisible,'),
(340, 2, 2, 'Yea, living, incorruptible,'),
(340, 2, 3, 'Thy grace and glory, truth and love'),
(340, 2, 4, 'Now seen in Christ, all praise above.'),
(340, 2, 5, 'Thee would we worship and extol,'),
(340, 2, 6, 'O blessed God, soon all in all!'),
(341, 1, 1, 'O blessed Saviour, is Thy love'),
(341, 1, 2, 'So great, so full, so free?'),
(341, 1, 3, 'Fain would we have our souls, our hearts,'),
(341, 1, 4, 'Our minds engaged with Thee.'),
(341, 2, 1, 'We love Thee for the glorious worth'),
(341, 2, 2, 'Which in Thyself we see;'),
(341, 2, 3, 'We love Thee for that shameful cross,'),
(341, 2, 4, 'Endured so patiently.'),
(341, 3, 1, 'No greater love can man display'),
(341, 3, 2, 'Than for His friends to die;'),
(341, 3, 3, 'Thus faithful to Thine own wast Thou:'),
(341, 3, 4, 'What love with Thine can vie?'),
(341, 4, 1, 'Thou like Thy brethren wouldst become,'),
(341, 4, 2, 'And here a Suff''rer be;'),
(341, 4, 3, 'In flesh and blood Thou didst take part,'),
(341, 4, 4, 'Through death to set us free.'),
(341, 5, 1, 'As man, O Lord, it was not good'),
(341, 5, 2, 'That Thou alone shouldst be;'),
(341, 5, 3, 'Fruit of Thy death, Thou hast secured'),
(341, 5, 4, 'A helpmate meet for Thee.'),
(341, 6, 1, 'O Lord, we treasure in our souls'),
(341, 6, 2, 'The memory of Thy love;'),
(341, 6, 3, 'And ever shall Thy Name to us'),
(341, 6, 4, 'A grateful odour prove.'),
(342, 1, 1, 'O Lord, the knowledge of Thy love'),
(342, 1, 2, 'Doth bow our hearts to Thee above;'),
(342, 1, 3, 'Before Thy face we prostrate fall,'),
(342, 1, 4, 'Whose wondrous glory shines for all.'),
(342, 1, 5, 'We worship, praise Thee and adore,'),
(342, 1, 6, 'Exalt Thy Name for evermore!'),
(342, 2, 1, 'Thy church, Thy body and Thy bride,'),
(342, 2, 2, 'With Thee, the Christ, identified -'),
(342, 2, 3, 'Espoused to Thee, a virgin chaste,'),
(342, 2, 4, 'While travelling still this dreary waste -'),
(342, 2, 5, 'Finds in Thyself her hope, her all!'),
(342, 2, 6, 'She waits to hear her Bridegroom call.'),
(342, 3, 1, 'He comes! The longed-for, glorious Lord,'),
(342, 3, 2, 'Whose Name by all shall be adored!'),
(342, 3, 3, 'He comes to take His bride on high,'),
(342, 3, 4, 'To share to all eternity'),
(342, 3, 5, 'The fruits of God''s eternal plan,'),
(342, 3, 6, 'Before the age of time began.'),
(342, 4, 1, 'The heav''n and earth, the sea and land,'),
(342, 4, 2, 'Display the pow''r of God''s own hand,'),
(342, 4, 3, 'And all His matchless moral ways'),
(342, 4, 4, 'Redound for ever to His praise;'),
(342, 4, 5, 'But in this glorious mystery'),
(342, 4, 6, 'Unfathomable love we see.'),
(343, 1, 1, '"Lord, what is man?" ''Tis Christ who died,'),
(343, 1, 2, 'And all Thy nature glorified;'),
(343, 1, 3, 'Thy righteousness and grace displayed'),
(343, 1, 4, 'When He for sins atonement made;'),
(343, 1, 5, 'Obedient unto death, was slain -'),
(343, 1, 6, 'Worthy is He o''er all to reign!'),
(343, 2, 1, 'Thy counsels ere the world began');
INSERT INTO `hymn_line` (`hymn_no`, `vers_no`, `line_no`, `line_text`) VALUES (343, 2, 2, 'All centred in the Son of man;'),
(343, 2, 3, 'Head of the church His destined place,'),
(343, 2, 4, 'Thy glory radiant in His face.'),
(343, 2, 5, 'To Him, enthroned in majesty,'),
(343, 2, 6, 'Let every creature bend the knee!'),
(343, 3, 1, 'Worthy, O Son of man, art Thou'),
(343, 3, 2, 'Of every crown that decks Thy brow;'),
(343, 3, 3, 'Worthy art Thou to be adored'),
(343, 3, 4, 'And owned as universal Lord;'),
(343, 3, 5, 'O hasten that long-promised day'),
(343, 3, 6, 'When all shall own Thy rightful sway!'),
(344, 1, 1, 'Wilt Thou come, or wilt thou linger?'),
(344, 1, 2, '''Tis the Saviour calls;'),
(344, 1, 3, 'Death and darkness are around thee;'),
(344, 1, 4, 'Sin enthralls.'),
(344, 2, 1, 'Thou may''st come; the vilest sinner'),
(344, 2, 2, 'May in Christ confide.'),
(344, 2, 3, 'Thou art welcome, for to save thee'),
(344, 2, 4, 'Jesus died.'),
(344, 3, 1, 'See the blood, and hear Him speaking'),
(344, 3, 2, 'Of redemption done;'),
(344, 3, 3, 'And on glory''s heights behold Him,'),
(344, 3, 4, 'God''s own Son.'),
(344, 4, 1, 'Hear Him speak the word of pardon;'),
(344, 4, 2, 'Trust in Him who died;'),
(344, 4, 3, 'And thy heart shall lose its burden,'),
(344, 4, 4, 'By His side.'),
(345, 1, 1, 'O Lord, do Thou our souls inspire'),
(345, 1, 2, 'With fervent love and deep desire,'),
(345, 1, 3, 'To follow Thee, Thy Name to own,'),
(345, 1, 4, 'As Thy disciples thus be known.'),
(345, 2, 1, 'Thou hast Thy life for us laid down,'),
(345, 2, 2, 'Laid up, for us, a righteous crown.'),
(345, 2, 3, 'Should we not then devoted be,'),
(345, 2, 4, 'In full committal, Lord, to Thee?'),
(345, 3, 1, 'O Lord, do Thou our hearts prepare'),
(345, 3, 2, 'To rise to meet Thee in the air;'),
(345, 3, 3, 'Our bodies changed, our spirits free,'),
(345, 3, 4, 'To dwell in glory, Lord, with Thee.'),
(345, 4, 1, 'A great assembling shout ''twill be,'),
(345, 4, 2, 'An answer meet to Calvary.'),
(345, 4, 3, 'Thou wilt in triumph lead Thine own,'),
(345, 4, 4, 'To take, with Thee, Thy rightful throne.'),
(346, 1, 1, 'Lord Jesus, Thou art worthy'),
(346, 1, 2, 'Of worship and of praise;'),
(346, 1, 3, 'Eternal are Thy glories'),
(346, 1, 4, 'That fill our raptured gaze.'),
(346, 2, 1, 'The greatness of Thy Person'),
(346, 2, 2, 'Transcends our power to tell;'),
(346, 2, 3, 'All fulness of the Godhead'),
(346, 2, 4, 'In Thee, O Lord, doth dwell.'),
(346, 3, 1, 'Creator, Thou, of all things,'),
(346, 3, 2, 'God''s glory shines in thee;'),
(346, 3, 3, 'Expression of His substance,'),
(346, 3, 4, 'To Thee we bow the knee -'),
(346, 4, 1, 'Firstborn of all creation,'),
(346, 4, 2, 'And Firstborn from the dead,'),
(346, 4, 3, 'Pre-eminent in all things,'),
(346, 4, 4, 'Th''assembly''s glorious Head!'),
(347, 1, 1, 'The bread and cup, O Lord, recall'),
(347, 1, 2, 'that sacrifice supreme, when all'),
(347, 1, 3, 'The floods their voice did raise;'),
(347, 1, 4, 'Their holy import we discern,'),
(347, 1, 5, 'Thy suff''ring love afresh would learn,'),
(347, 1, 6, 'Proved on that day of days.'),
(347, 2, 1, 'All question of our moral stain'),
(347, 2, 2, 'Thou didst resolve when Thou didst drain'),
(347, 2, 3, 'That cup of bitt''rest woe:'),
(347, 2, 4, 'So surely, that our hearts are free'),
(347, 2, 5, 'To yield themselves adoringly'),
(347, 2, 6, 'In love''s eternal flow.'),
(347, 3, 1, 'Borne in Thy heart through death''s dark tide'),
(347, 3, 2, '(The travail Thine), with Thee we died,'),
(347, 3, 3, 'In Thee we rise on high;'),
(347, 3, 4, 'With hearts now filled with glory''s light,'),
(347, 3, 5, 'We tread our path through earth''s dark night,'),
(347, 3, 6, 'Where Thou our Lord didst die.'),
(348, 1, 1, 'How good and great, O Father,'),
(348, 1, 2, 'Thy wondrous thoughts are shown!'),
(348, 1, 3, 'Concealed from wise and prudent,'),
(348, 1, 4, 'Revealed to babes alone.'),
(348, 1, 5, 'But having understanding,'),
(348, 1, 6, 'And Spirit-given joy,'),
(348, 1, 7, 'To bless Thee, God our Father,'),
(348, 1, 8, 'We heart and voice employ.'),
(348, 2, 1, 'Father, Thine own Son praised Thee,'),
(348, 2, 2, 'Of heav''n and earth the Lord!'),
(348, 2, 3, 'Thy sovereign operations'),
(348, 2, 4, 'Great joy to Thee afford:'),
(348, 2, 5, 'For all those coming to Him -'),
(348, 2, 6, 'The meek and lowly Man -'),
(348, 2, 7, 'Are held by Him for ever,'),
(348, 2, 8, 'The fruit of Thy great plan.'),
(348, 3, 1, 'Each knowing Thee as Father -'),
(348, 3, 2, 'Revealed so by the Son -'),
(348, 3, 3, 'We share His joy before Thee'),
(348, 3, 4, 'In all that Thou hast done.'),
(348, 3, 5, 'The Son Thou, Father, knowest;'),
(348, 3, 6, 'But in that Man so blest,'),
(348, 3, 7, 'To whom Thou''st given all things,'),
(348, 3, 8, 'Our souls find perfect rest.'),
(349, 1, 1, 'We hear the words of love,'),
(349, 1, 2, 'We gaze upon the blood,'),
(349, 1, 3, 'We see the mighty Sacrifice,'),
(349, 1, 4, 'And we have peace with God.'),
(349, 2, 1, '''Tis everlasting peace,'),
(349, 2, 2, 'Sure as Jehovah''s Name;'),
(349, 2, 3, '''Tis stable as His steadfast throne,'),
(349, 2, 4, 'For evermore the same.'),
(349, 3, 1, 'Our love is oft-times low,'),
(349, 3, 2, 'Our joy still ebbs and flows;'),
(349, 3, 3, 'But peace with Him remains the same;'),
(349, 3, 4, 'No change Jehovah knows.'),
(349, 4, 1, 'We change - He changes not,'),
(349, 4, 2, 'Though changing years roll by;'),
(349, 4, 3, 'His love, not ours, the resting-place,'),
(349, 4, 4, 'We on His truth rely.'),
(349, 5, 1, 'The cross still stands unchanged,'),
(349, 5, 2, 'Though heav''n is now His home;'),
(349, 5, 3, 'The mighty stone is rolled away,'),
(349, 5, 4, 'For He has left the tomb.'),
(349, 6, 1, 'We know He liveth now'),
(349, 6, 2, 'At God''s right hand above;'),
(349, 6, 3, 'We know the throne on which He sits,'),
(349, 6, 4, 'We know His truth and love.'),
(350, 1, 1, 'We hail Thee, Lord, our glorious Head,'),
(350, 1, 2, 'Victorious Firstborn from the dead;'),
(350, 1, 3, 'Exalted far beyond the skies,'),
(350, 1, 4, 'To Thee our praises now would rise.'),
(350, 2, 1, 'Received in glory bright up there,'),
(350, 2, 2, 'The Father''s greetings, honours rare,'),
(350, 2, 3, 'Are heaped upon His Son''s blest brow;'),
(350, 2, 4, 'He is the mighty Victor now.'),
(350, 3, 1, 'The Father''s throne by Him is shared,'),
(350, 3, 2, 'Whose nature He, the Son, declared;'),
(350, 3, 3, 'Whose will He did, the cost how great!'),
(350, 3, 4, 'His worthiness we celebrate.'),
(351, 1, 1, 'Holy Comforter, who guidest'),
(351, 1, 2, 'Those who seek Thine aid divine,'),
(351, 1, 3, 'Who within the saints abidest,'),
(351, 1, 4, 'May Thy light among us shine.'),
(351, 2, 1, 'Precious things to Christ belonging,'),
(351, 2, 2, 'Brought to us in love by Thee,'),
(351, 2, 3, 'Fill our souls with holy longing'),
(351, 2, 4, 'Of His glory more to see.'),
(351, 3, 1, 'Grant us subject minds, attentive'),
(351, 3, 2, 'As the truth Thou dost unfold;'),
(351, 3, 3, 'May our hearts be more retentive,'),
(351, 3, 4, 'Treasuries for wealth untold.'),
(352, 1, 1, 'O Lord, the joy on union,'),
(352, 1, 2, 'And Thine embrace, call forth'),
(352, 1, 3, 'Our full appreciation'),
(352, 1, 4, 'Of Thy surpassing worth.'),
(352, 2, 1, 'The bride, with Thee in nearness,'),
(352, 2, 2, 'Adds lustre to the scene'),
(352, 2, 3, 'Where all Thy power and greatness'),
(352, 2, 4, 'In headship''s place are seen.'),
(352, 3, 1, 'Th''assembly, Lord, Thy body,'),
(352, 3, 2, 'As joined to Thee above,'),
(352, 3, 3, 'Responds with deep affection -'),
(352, 3, 4, 'At rest in Thy great love.'),
(352, 4, 1, 'Thus in this blest relation,'),
(352, 4, 2, 'With one harmonious strain'),
(352, 4, 3, 'We join with adoration,'),
(352, 4, 4, 'Thy praises to proclaim.'),
(353, 1, 1, 'What will it be to dwell above,'),
(353, 1, 2, 'And with Thee, Lord of glory, reign,'),
(353, 1, 3, 'Since the blest knowledge of Thy love'),
(353, 1, 4, 'So brightens all this dreary plain?'),
(353, 1, 5, 'No heart can think, no tongue can tell,'),
(353, 1, 6, 'What joy ''twill be with Thee to dwell.'),
(353, 2, 1, 'When left this scene of faith and strife,'),
(353, 2, 2, 'And flesh and sense deceive no more;'),
(353, 2, 3, 'When we shall see Thee, Prince of life,'),
(353, 2, 4, 'And all Thy works of grace explore;'),
(353, 2, 5, 'What heights and depths of love divine'),
(353, 2, 6, 'Will there through endless ages shine!'),
(353, 3, 1, 'And God has fixed the happy day'),
(353, 3, 2, 'When the last tear shall dim our eyes,'),
(353, 3, 3, 'When He will wipe these tears away,'),
(353, 3, 4, 'And fill our hearts with glad surprise;'),
(353, 3, 5, 'To hear Thy voice and see Thy face,'),
(353, 3, 6, 'And know the fulness of God''s grace.'),
(354, 1, 1, 'We speak of the grace of our God,'),
(354, 1, 2, 'So boundless, so rich, and so free;'),
(354, 1, 3, 'But what will it profit Thy soul'),
(354, 1, 4, 'Unless ''tis relied on by thee?'),
(354, 2, 1, 'We speak of salvation and love,'),
(354, 2, 2, 'By the Father in Jesus made known;'),
