(400, 3, 4, 'Filled in the ocean of that love, a never-ebbing tide.'),
(401, 1, 1, 'Spirit of grace, O Thou whose hidden might'),
(401, 1, 2, 'Sustains us day by day the whole way through,'),
(401, 1, 3, 'We bless Thee for Thy service, and unite'),
(401, 1, 4, 'In rend''ring now the homage that is due.'),
(401, 2, 1, 'Spirit of truth, ''tis Thou who lead''st us on'),
(401, 2, 2, 'Into the fulness of God''s purpose here;'),
(401, 2, 3, 'Thou takest heav''nly glories of the Son,'),
(401, 2, 4, 'And bringest every precious feature near.'),
(401, 3, 1, 'Filled with the favour Thou dost make us prove,'),
(401, 3, 2, 'Spirit of life, with rev''rent hearts may we'),
(401, 3, 3, 'More skilfully in service learn to move,'),
(401, 3, 4, 'And for the power rely alone on Thee.'),
(401, 4, 1, 'Clothe us with that humility, we pray,'),
(401, 4, 2, 'That honours Thee and shows what Thou canst do;'),
(401, 4, 3, 'Grant that the lustre of th''eternal day -'),
(401, 4, 4, 'The day of God - shine in our hearts anew.'),
(402, 1, 1, 'Father, Son, and Holy Spirit -'),
(402, 1, 2, 'Blessed Name of Godhead known!'),
(402, 1, 3, 'We its fulness, power and blessing'),
(402, 1, 4, 'Claim in faith to be our own.'),
(402, 2, 1, 'Father, the desire we cherish'),
(402, 2, 2, 'To be sanctified by Thee;'),
(402, 2, 3, 'In Thy Name, Thy truth, kept holy,'),
(402, 2, 4, 'Joying in the Trinity.'),
(402, 3, 1, 'Owning Thy blest claim, Lord Jesus,'),
(402, 3, 2, 'May our households always be -'),
(402, 3, 3, 'To the Name as thus baptised -'),
(402, 3, 4, 'Held entirely, Lord, for Thee.'),
(402, 4, 1, 'From the world - its joys and pleasures -'),
(402, 4, 2, 'Wholly sep''rate would we live;'),
(402, 4, 3, 'In Thy power, O blessed Spirit,'),
(402, 4, 4, 'Walk in life which Thou dost give.'),
(403, 1, 1, 'Father, now we come before Thee,'),
(403, 1, 2, 'Humbly we would seek Thy face,'),
(403, 1, 3, 'While our thankful hearts adore Thee'),
(403, 1, 4, 'For Thy changeless love and grace.'),
(403, 2, 1, 'Nought can dim the cloudless favour'),
(403, 2, 2, 'Of the place in which we stand,'),
(403, 2, 3, 'Brought to Thee through Christ our Saviour,'),
(403, 2, 4, 'Kept by Thine almighty hand.'),
(403, 3, 1, 'Vain is fear since Thou art for us;'),
(403, 3, 2, 'All good gifts from Thee come down;');
INSERT INTO `hymn_line` (`hymn_no`, `vers_no`, `line_no`, `line_text`) VALUES (403, 3, 3, 'Every day that passes o''er us'),
(403, 3, 4, 'With Thy goodness Thou dost crown.'),
(403, 4, 1, 'May we here Thy will be doing,'),
(403, 4, 2, 'In Thy service faithful be,'),
(403, 4, 3, 'Day by day our path pursuing'),
(403, 4, 4, 'With the help that comes from Thee!'),
(403, 5, 1, 'With The heav''nly beams enlighten'),
(403, 5, 2, 'Every step along the way;'),
(403, 5, 3, 'May our path go on and brighten'),
(403, 5, 4, 'Unto Thine eternal day!'),
(404, 1, 1, 'On His Father''s throne is seated'),
(404, 1, 2, 'Christ the Lord, the Living One,'),
(404, 1, 3, 'All His toil on earth completed,'),
(404, 1, 4, 'All His work for sinners done;'),
(404, 1, 5, 'In the glory'),
(404, 1, 6, 'See Him, God''s beloved Son.'),
(404, 2, 1, 'Man the cross to him awarded,'),
(404, 2, 2, 'Man the Saviour crucified;'),
(404, 2, 3, 'This worlds judgment stands recorded,'),
(404, 2, 4, 'God''s own nature glorified.'),
(404, 2, 5, 'By the glory'),
(404, 2, 6, 'Christ was claimed, on earth who died.'),
(404, 3, 1, 'Every knee shall bow before Him,'),
(404, 3, 2, 'Every tongue confess His Name;'),
(404, 3, 3, 'Ransomed myriads shall adore Him'),
(404, 3, 4, 'Who endured the sinner''s shame.'),
(404, 3, 5, 'From the glory'),
(404, 3, 6, 'God doth now His worth proclaim.'),
(405, 1, 1, 'To God, in highest power supreme,'),
(405, 1, 2, 'To God o''er all, the greatest theme,'),
(405, 1, 3, 'To God, by heav''nly hosts adored,'),
(405, 1, 4, 'To God, of all the sovereign Lord -'),
(405, 1, 5, 'Our adoration let us bring,'),
(405, 1, 6, 'And let our hearts His worship sing;'),
(405, 1, 7, 'With grateful love our voices raise,'),
(405, 1, 8, 'And every tongue proclaim His praise!'),
(405, 2, 1, 'Thou gav''st Thy Son for us to die,'),
(405, 2, 2, 'Revealing Thy great heart thereby,'),
(405, 2, 3, 'Securing thus adoring love,'),
(405, 2, 4, 'Which now ascends to Thee above.'),
(405, 2, 5, 'What joy, O God, Thy heart must know'),
(405, 2, 6, 'To see Thy lovers here below,'),
(405, 2, 7, 'Made like Thy Son by grace divine,'),
(405, 2, 8, 'With hearts responding unto Thine!'),
(406, 1, 1, 'O blessed God, our souls are moved as one'),
(406, 1, 2, 'To render praise and wider glory still;'),
(406, 1, 3, 'Our minds are filled with all that Thou hast done'),
(406, 1, 4, 'In working out the counsel of Thy will.'),
(406, 2, 1, 'We bow in adoration, for we know'),
(406, 2, 2, 'It was Thy thought before the world began'),
(406, 2, 3, 'To fill a scene where endless praise should flow,'),
(406, 2, 4, 'And share Thy rest eternally with man.'),
(406, 3, 1, 'And by the Spirit now we touch that rest,'),
(406, 3, 2, 'And see, O God, the end of all Thy ways;'),
(406, 3, 3, 'We stand in Christ as those Thy love has blest,'),
(406, 3, 4, 'To serve Thee now and richest anthems raise.'),
(406, 4, 1, 'We thus extol afresh Thy wondrous name,'),
(406, 4, 2, 'And bow before Thy glory all divine.'),
(406, 4, 3, 'We worship still, while gladdened hearts exclaim -'),
(406, 4, 4, '"Thou canst be hindered in no thought of Thine!"'),
(407, 1, 1, 'O God, Thy grace no limit knows,'),
(407, 1, 2, 'Pure and unfathomed is Thy love;'),
(407, 1, 3, 'Thy boundless mercy freely flows,'),
(407, 1, 4, 'Since Jesus came from heav''n above'),
(407, 1, 5, 'And died - our souls from sin to free -'),
(407, 1, 6, 'When we were lost and far from Thee.'),
(407, 2, 1, 'Jesus, the Lord, our ransom paid'),
(407, 2, 2, 'In matchless condescending grace!'),
(407, 2, 3, 'Came to the world His hands had made,'),
(407, 2, 4, 'And stooped to take the sinner''s place.'),
(407, 2, 5, 'The just One for the unjust died;'),
(407, 2, 6, 'Thy holy claims are satisfied.'),
(407, 3, 1, 'But ris''n on high, for evermore'),
(407, 3, 2, 'Jesus the mighty Saviour lives;'),
(407, 3, 3, 'Blessing from Thine exhaustless store'),
(407, 3, 4, 'To all who trust Him now He gives.'),
(407, 3, 5, 'Through Him we know Thy love divine;'),
(407, 3, 6, 'In Him we see Thy glory shine.'),
(407, 4, 1, 'The Holy Spirit here below'),
(407, 4, 2, 'Sheds in our hearts Thy wondrous love,'),
(407, 4, 3, 'And gives us even now to know'),
(407, 4, 4, 'Our glorious place with Christ above.'),
(407, 4, 5, 'Thus pardoned, cleansed and freed from blame,'),
(407, 4, 6, 'O blessed God, we praise Thy Name!'),
(408, 1, 1, 'Thou Holy Comforter, we joy in thee,'),
(408, 1, 2, 'Sent down in answer to our Lord''s request.'),
(408, 1, 3, 'Deep were Thy feelings when Thou cam''st to be'),
(408, 1, 4, 'With us for ever from that day so blest!'),
(408, 2, 1, 'Spirit of truth, in Thee our minds find rest,'),
(408, 2, 2, 'While here in this dark, unresponsive scene;'),
(408, 2, 3, 'Thou art for ever with us; O how blest'),
(408, 2, 4, 'To know Thee even though Thou art unseen!'),
(408, 3, 1, 'No eye has seen nor ear has ever heard,'),
(408, 3, 2, 'Nor heart of man is great enough to hold'),
(408, 3, 3, 'Those wondrous things in love by God prepared,'),
(408, 3, 4, 'Which Thou, blest Spirit, lovest to unfold.'),
(408, 4, 1, 'Nor is this all, for Thou the Earnest art'),
(408, 4, 2, 'Of bliss to come, and giv''st us even here'),
(408, 4, 3, 'To enter now our glorious heav''nly part,'),
(408, 4, 4, 'And taste the joys of that eternal sphere!'),
(409, 1, 1, 'Come! for the Father speaks to thee from heaven,'),
(409, 1, 2, 'In Jesus'' death His heart of love was told;'),
(409, 1, 3, 'Since He His only Son for thee has given,'),
(409, 1, 4, 'His bounteous hand no blessing would withhold.'),
(409, 2, 1, 'Come! for the Saviour speaks, in grace appealing,'),
(409, 2, 2, 'He waits to pardon, and to cleanse thy soul;'),
(409, 2, 3, 'His precious blood alone can give thee healing,'),
(409, 2, 4, 'Can wash thee from thy sins and make thee whole.'),
(409, 3, 1, 'Come! for the Spirit speaks of Christ in glory;'),
(409, 3, 2, 'In tender patience still He waits on thee.'),
(409, 3, 3, 'Hark to His voice, and heed the wondrous story'),
(409, 3, 4, 'Of full salvation, measureless and free.'),
(409, 4, 1, 'Come now in faith, by God Himself invited!'),
(409, 4, 2, 'He longs thy heart with heav''nly joys to fill;'),
(409, 4, 3, 'For He, though oft His goodness thou hast slighted,'),
(409, 4, 4, 'In grace and love unwearied seeks thee still.'),
(409, 5, 1, 'To Jesus come, and as thy Saviour own Him,'),
(409, 5, 2, 'To Him confessing all thy guilt and woe;'),
(409, 5, 3, 'As Lord and Master in thy heart enthrone Him,'),
(409, 5, 4, 'Life everlasting, peace and joy to know.'),
(410, 1, 1, 'On the Lamb our souls are resting,'),
(410, 1, 2, 'What His love no tongue can say;'),
(410, 1, 3, 'All our sins, so great, so many,'),
(410, 1, 4, 'In His blood are washed away.'),
(410, 2, 1, 'Sweetest rest and peace have filled us,'),
(410, 2, 2, 'Sweeter praise than tongue can tell;'),
(410, 2, 3, 'God is satisfied with Jesus,'),
(410, 2, 4, 'We are satisfied as well.'),
(410, 3, 1, 'Conscience now no more condemns us,'),
(410, 3, 2, 'For His own most precious blood'),
(410, 3, 3, 'Once for all has washed and cleansed us,'),
(410, 3, 4, 'Cleansed us in the sight of God.'),
(410, 4, 1, 'Filled with this sweet peace for ever,'),
(410, 4, 2, 'On we go, through strife and care,'),
(410, 4, 3, 'Till we find that peace around us'),
(410, 4, 4, 'In the Lamb''s high glory there.'),
(410, 5, 1, 'On the living Lord believing,'),
(410, 5, 2, 'We have righteousness and peace.'),
(410, 5, 3, 'By the Holy Spirit given'),
(410, 5, 4, 'We have joys that never cease.'),
(411, 1, 1, 'Lord ! let us wait for Thee alone:'),
(411, 1, 2, 'Our life be only this -'),
(411, 1, 3, 'To serve Thee here on earth, unknown;'),
(411, 1, 4, 'Then share Thy heavenly bliss.'),
(411, 2, 1, 'Lord, we would wait, in labour still'),
(411, 2, 2, 'In Thy blest service here:'),
(411, 2, 3, 'What Thou hast giv''n us to fulfil -'),
(411, 2, 4, 'Thy will - to us is dear!'),
(411, 3, 1, 'We well can wait! Thou waitest yet'),
(411, 3, 2, 'The word of that dread hour,'),
(411, 3, 3, 'Which shall Thy foes for ever set'),
(411, 3, 4, 'As footstool of Thy power.'),
(411, 4, 1, 'Yet, Lord! were one Thy will fulfilled,'),
(411, 4, 2, 'How better far with thee,'),
(411, 4, 3, 'With Thee, our joy, our strength, our shield,'),
(411, 4, 4, 'In cloudless light to be.'),
(411, 5, 1, 'Lord be it soon! Thou know''st our heart,'),
(411, 5, 2, 'In this sad world, no rest'),
(411, 5, 3, 'Can find nor wish but where Thou art:'),
(411, 5, 4, 'That rest itself possessed!'),
(412, 1, 1, 'Lord Spirit, blest, of Thee we''re taught,'),
(412, 1, 2, 'By Thee indwelt, and through Thee brought'),
(412, 1, 3, 'To know the truth Thou dost confide'),
(412, 1, 4, 'To subject hearts, whom Thou dost guide.'),
(412, 2, 1, 'Thy service doth our praise compel,'),
(412, 2, 2, 'As with and in us Thou dost dwell;'),
(412, 2, 3, 'Spirit divine, our hearts we raise'),
(412, 2, 4, 'In joyful worship, thankful praise.'),
(412, 3, 1, 'All things of Jesus Thou dost know,'),
(412, 3, 2, 'Their glorious greatness to us show;'),
(412, 3, 3, 'By Thee, blest Spirit, now adored,'),
(412, 3, 4, 'We contemplate the Christ, our Lord.'),
(412, 4, 1, 'Where''er, Lord Spirit, Thou shalt be,'),
(412, 4, 2, 'For us there is sweet liberty.'),
(412, 4, 3, 'Thus we upon His glory gaze,'),
(412, 4, 4, 'Now shining in His unveiled face.'),
(412, 5, 1, 'From glory unto glory brought,'),
(412, 5, 2, 'And by Thy perfect work inwrought,'),
(412, 5, 3, 'We see the glory that doth shine'),
(412, 5, 4, 'In His blest countenance divine.'),
(413, 1, 1, '"A little while" - the Lord shall come,'),
(413, 1, 2, 'And we shall journey here no more;'),
(413, 1, 3, 'He''ll take us to His Father''s home,'),
(413, 1, 4, 'Where He for us is gone before,'),
(413, 1, 5, 'To dwell with Him, to see His face,'),
(413, 1, 6, 'And sing the glories of His grace.'),
(413, 2, 1, '"A little while" - He''ll come again;'),
(413, 2, 2, 'Let us the precious hours redeem;'),
(413, 2, 3, 'No more to grieve and give Him pain,'),
(413, 2, 4, 'Our joy to serve and follow Him.'),
(413, 2, 5, 'Watching and ready may we be,'),
(413, 2, 6, 'As those that wait their Lord to see.'),
(413, 3, 1, '"A little while" - ''twill soon be past;'),
(413, 3, 2, 'Why should we shun the promised cross?'),
(413, 3, 3, 'O let us in His footsteps haste,'),
(413, 3, 4, 'Counting for Him all else but loss!'),
(413, 3, 5, 'For how will recompense His smile'),
(413, 3, 6, 'The suff''rings of this "little while!"'),
(413, 4, 1, '"A little while" - come, Saviour, come!'),
(413, 4, 2, 'For Thee Thy saints have tarried long;'),
(413, 4, 3, 'O take Thy waiting pilgrims home,'),
(413, 4, 4, 'To sing the new eternal song,'),
(413, 4, 5, 'To see Thy glory, and to be'),
(413, 4, 6, 'In everything conformed to Thee!'),
(414, 1, 1, 'Once from glory''s height descending,'),
(414, 1, 2, 'To this earth the Saviour came;'),
(414, 1, 3, 'Here in grace His pathway wending,'),
(414, 1, 4, 'Here He magnified God''s name.'),
(414, 1, 5, 'Lowly Saviour!'),
(414, 1, 6, 'We would still His grace proclaim.'),
(414, 2, 1, 'On to Calv''ry''s shame and suff''ring,'),
(414, 2, 2, 'He to death the path did tread;'),
(414, 2, 3, 'There for sin the perfect Off''ring,'),
(414, 2, 4, 'On the cross His blood was shed.'),
(414, 2, 5, 'Wondrous Saviour!'),
(414, 2, 6, 'Dying in the sinner''s stead.'),
(414, 3, 1, 'Out from death, His work completed,'),
(414, 3, 2, 'Burst the portals of the grave;'),
(414, 3, 3, 'High at God''s right hand now seated,'),
(414, 3, 4, 'He can e''en the vilest save.'),
(414, 3, 5, 'Glorious Saviour!'),
(414, 3, 6, '''Twas in love His all He gave.'),
(414, 4, 1, 'Still he waits in grace transcending,'),
(414, 4, 2, 'He for thee has tarried long;'),
(414, 4, 3, 'Bids thee share in joys unending,'),
(414, 4, 4, 'Join e''en now in heav''n''s blest song.'),
(414, 4, 5, 'Worthy Saviour!'),
(414, 4, 6, 'Theme of all the ransomed throng.'),
(415, 1, 1, 'O Lord, what burdens Thou didst bear!'),
(415, 1, 2, 'Our load was laid on Thee;'),
(415, 1, 3, 'Thou stoodest for the sinner there'),
(415, 1, 4, 'To bear all ill for me.'),
(415, 1, 5, 'A Victim led, Thy blood was shed;'),
(415, 1, 6, 'Now there''s no load for me.'),
(415, 2, 1, 'Death and the curse were in our cup,'),
(415, 2, 2, 'O Lord, ''twas full for Thee!'),
(415, 2, 3, 'But Thou hast drained the last dark drop,'),
(415, 2, 4, '''Tis empty now for me.'),
(415, 2, 5, 'That bitter cup - love drank it up;'),
(415, 2, 6, 'Left but the love for me.'),
(415, 3, 1, 'The tempest''s awful voice was heard:'),
(415, 3, 2, 'O Lord, it broke on Thee!'),
(415, 3, 3, 'Thine open bosom was my ward,'),
(415, 3, 4, 'It bore the storm for me.'),
(415, 3, 5, 'Thy form was scarred, thy visage marred;'),
(415, 3, 6, 'Now cloudless peace for me.'),
(415, 4, 1, 'For me, Lord Jesus, Thou hast died,'),
(415, 4, 2, 'And I have died with Thee;'),
(415, 4, 3, 'Thou''rt ris''n: my bands are all untied;'),
(415, 4, 4, 'And now Thou liv''st in me.'),
(415, 4, 5, 'The Father''s face in radiant grace'),
(415, 4, 6, 'Shines now in light on me.'),
(416, 1, 1, 'Father, now in adoration'),
(416, 1, 2, 'Rev''rently we sing to Thee;'),
(416, 1, 3, 'Thy supremacy discerning'),
(416, 1, 4, 'In love''s blest economy.'),
(416, 1, 5, 'Glorious Thou in revelation,'),
(416, 1, 6, 'Greatness over all Thy part;'),
(416, 1, 7, 'Object of eternal worship'),
(416, 1, 8, 'By Thy many sons Thou art.'),
(416, 2, 1, 'Thou dost work all things according'),
(416, 2, 2, 'To the counsel of Thy will;'),
(416, 2, 3, 'Blessing us in the Beloved,'),
(416, 2, 4, 'Causing praise Thine ear to fill.'),
(416, 2, 5, 'Wider still Thy blessing floweth,'),
(416, 2, 6, 'Every family named of Thee,'),
(416, 2, 7, 'Thou, the Source of all, the Father,'),
(416, 2, 8, 'Giving all in life to be.'),
(416, 3, 1, 'By the Spirit we adore Thee,'),
(416, 3, 2, 'In the Son to us made known;'),
(416, 3, 3, 'Joying in thy love and favour,'),
(416, 3, 4, 'In Thy grace and goodness shown.'),
(416, 3, 5, 'Blessed is Thy holy presence,'),
(416, 3, 6, 'Portion of the saints in light;'),
(416, 3, 7, 'Unto Thee be ever glory,'),
(416, 3, 8, 'Worship, honour, praise and might!'),
(417, 1, 1, 'Who will hearken to the story'),
(417, 1, 2, 'Of God''s wondrous love and grace?'),
(417, 1, 3, 'Told out now in all its fulness'),
(417, 1, 4, 'To the sons of Adam''s race.'),
(417, 1, 5, 'Whosoever - glorious message'),
(417, 1, 6, 'From the throne of God above -'),
(417, 1, 7, 'Trusts in Him who died to save him,'),
(417, 1, 8, 'Proves the sweetness of God''s love.'),
(417, 2, 1, 'Who will hearken to the Saviour?'),
(417, 2, 2, 'As in grace He calls today?'),
(417, 2, 3, 'Who accept God''s free forgiveness,'),
(417, 2, 4, 'Own Christ Lord without delay?'),
(417, 2, 5, 'Who will yield in full obedience'),
(417, 2, 6, 'To God''s Son enthroned on high?'),
(417, 2, 7, 'He would give the Holy Spirit,'),
(417, 2, 8, 'Fill the heart with peace and joy.'),
(417, 3, 1, 'Who will hearken to the Spirit,'),
(417, 3, 2, 'From iniquity depart,'),
(417, 3, 3, 'Be a vessel for the Master,'),
(417, 3, 4, 'Sanctified and pure in heart?'),
(417, 3, 5, 'Overcoming here ''midst evil,'),
(417, 3, 6, 'Cleaving fast to what is true,'),
(417, 3, 7, 'Answer to Christ''s present longing,'),
(417, 3, 8, 'Yield to Him the homage due?'),
(418, 1, 1, 'A Jesus, blessed Saviour,'),
(418, 1, 2, 'As we Thy beauty see'),
(418, 1, 3, 'We gladly do Thee homage,'),
(418, 1, 4, 'And glory give to Thee.'),
(418, 2, 1, 'Thou by th''eternal Spirit'),
(418, 2, 2, 'Thyself didst offer up;'),
(418, 2, 3, 'In perfect, full obedience'),
(418, 2, 4, 'Didst take that awful cup!'),
(418, 3, 1, 'How pleasing to the Father,'),
(418, 3, 2, 'Whose will was fully done!'),
(418, 3, 3, 'How honoured by Thy people,'),
(418, 3, 4, 'Beloved, holy One!'),
(418, 4, 1, 'Let hosts of heav''n acclaim Thee!'),
(418, 4, 2, 'Let mortals shout for joy!'),
(418, 4, 3, 'The lips of all Thy lovers'),
(418, 4, 4, 'Eternal praise employ.'),
(419, 1, 1, 'Lord, Thou art with me!'),
(419, 1, 2, 'Whom shall I fear?'),
(419, 1, 3, 'Who then can harm me'),
(419, 1, 4, 'Whilst Thou art near?'),
(419, 1, 5, 'Under Thy shadow'),
(419, 1, 6, 'Is my retreat;'),
(419, 1, 7, 'There to my taste, Lord,'),
(419, 1, 8, 'Thy fruit is sweet.'),
(419, 2, 1, 'Lord, Thou art with me,'),
(419, 2, 2, 'And Thou dost give'),
(419, 2, 3, 'Strength for the journey,'),
(419, 2, 4, 'Grace now to live.'),
(419, 2, 5, 'Mercies each morning'),
(419, 2, 6, 'Thou dost renew;'),
(419, 2, 7, 'And for my prospect,'),
(419, 2, 8, 'Thy rest in view.'),
(419, 3, 1, 'Lord, Thou art with me;'),
(419, 3, 2, 'Onward I move;'),
(419, 3, 3, 'Each day I''m proving'),
(419, 3, 4, 'More of Thy love.'),
(419, 3, 5, 'Now thou art training,'),
(419, 3, 6, 'Setting me free'),
(419, 3, 7, 'From all that hinders,'),
(419, 3, 8, 'To dwell with Thee.'),
(420, 1, 1, 'Glory, glory, glory, praise and adoration!'),
(420, 1, 2, 'Hear the anthems swelling out through all eternity!'),
(420, 1, 3, 'Father, Son and Spirit - God in revelation -'),
(420, 1, 4, 'Prostrate each soul before the Deity!'),
(420, 2, 1, 'Father, source of glory, naming every fam''ly;'),
(420, 2, 2, 'And the Son upholding all by His almighty power;'),
(420, 2, 3, 'Holy Spirit, filling the vast scene of glory -'),
(420, 2, 4, 'O glorious Fulness, let our souls adore!'),
(420, 3, 1, 'God supreme, we worship now in holy splendour,'),
(420, 3, 2, 'Head of the vast scene of bliss, before Thy face we fall!'),
(420, 3, 3, 'Majesty and greatness, glory, praise and power'),
(420, 3, 4, 'To Thee belong, eternal Source of all!'),
(421, 1, 1, 'What will it be when all life''s toil is finished,'),
(421, 1, 2, 'And we have entered our eternal rest;'),
(421, 1, 3, 'When past for ever is the night of weeping,'),
(421, 1, 4, 'And with Thee, Lord, we are for ever blest!'),
(421, 2, 1, 'What will it be when all the strife is over,'),
(421, 2, 2, 'And all Thy saints, now scattered far and wide,'),
(421, 2, 3, 'Shall be without one shade of variation,'),
(421, 2, 4, 'All like Thee, Lord, united by Thy side!'),
(421, 3, 1, 'What will it be when sorrow''s day is ended,'),
(421, 3, 2, 'And pain and grief for ever pass away;'),
