(443, 3, 3, 'And, humbled low, confess their guilt'),
(443, 3, 4, 'Before the righteous Lord.'),
(443, 4, 1, 'No hope can on the law be built'),
(443, 4, 2, 'Of justifying grace;'),
(443, 4, 3, 'The law that shows the sinner''s guilt'),
(443, 4, 4, 'Condemns him to his face.'),
(443, 5, 1, 'With Christ the Lord we died to sin;'),
(443, 5, 2, 'With Him to life we rise -'),
(443, 5, 3, 'To life which, now begun on earth,'),
(443, 5, 4, 'Is perfect in the skies.'),
(444, 1, 1, 'O Lord, we would delight in Thee,'),
(444, 1, 2, 'And on Thy care depend;'),
(444, 1, 3, 'To Thee in every trouble flee,'),
(444, 1, 4, 'Our safe unfailing Friend.'),
(444, 2, 1, 'When human cisterns all are dried,'),
(444, 2, 2, 'Thy fulness is the same;'),
(444, 2, 3, 'May we with this be satisfied,'),
(444, 2, 4, 'And glory in Thy Name.'),
(444, 3, 1, 'What good in creatures may be found'),
(444, 3, 2, 'Is all derived from Thee;'),
(444, 3, 3, 'We must have all things and abound'),
(444, 3, 4, 'Through Thy sufficiency.'),
(444, 4, 1, 'Thou who hast made our hope secure'),
(444, 4, 2, 'Wilt here all good provide;'),
(444, 4, 3, 'While Thou art rich, can we be poor?'),
(444, 4, 4, 'Thou who for us hast died!'),
(444, 5, 1, 'O Lord, we cast each care on Thee,'),
(444, 5, 2, 'And triumph and adore;'),
(444, 5, 3, 'O that our great concern may be'),
(444, 5, 4, 'To love and praise Thee more!'),
(445, 1, 1, 'Jesus, the Lord, is ris''n'),
(445, 1, 2, 'Triumphant o''er the grave;'),
(445, 1, 3, 'For us He burst the pris''n,'),
(445, 1, 4, 'Almighty now to save!'),
(445, 1, 5, 'Captivity is captive led,'),
(445, 1, 6, 'Since Jesus liveth who was dead.'),
(445, 2, 1, 'Who to our charge shall lay'),
(445, 2, 2, 'Our sins before our God?'),
(445, 2, 3, 'Since all are washed away'),
(445, 2, 4, 'In Jesus'' precious blood.'),
(445, 2, 5, 'Captivity is captive led,'),
(445, 2, 6, 'Since Jesus liveth who was dead.'),
(445, 3, 1, 'Who now accuseth them'),
(445, 3, 2, 'Whom God hath justified?'),
(445, 3, 3, 'Or who shall those condemn'),
(445, 3, 4, 'For whom the Surety died?'),
(445, 3, 5, 'Captivity is captive led,'),
(445, 3, 6, 'Since Jesus liveth who was dead.'),
(445, 4, 1, 'Christ hath the ransom paid,'),
(445, 4, 2, 'The wondrous work is done;'),
(445, 4, 3, 'On Him our help is laid,'),
(445, 4, 4, 'The victory is won.'),
(445, 4, 5, 'Captivity is captive led,'),
(445, 4, 6, 'Since Jesus liveth who was dead.'),
(446, 1, 1, 'Just as I am - without one plea,'),
(446, 1, 2, 'But that Thy blood was shed for me.'),
(446, 1, 3, 'And that Thou bidst me come to Thee,'),
(446, 1, 4, 'O Lamb of God, I come!'),
(446, 2, 1, 'Just as I am - poor, wretched, blind;'),
(446, 2, 2, 'Sight, riches, healing of the mind,'),
(446, 2, 3, 'Yea, all I need, in Thee to find,'),
(446, 2, 4, 'O Lamb of God, I come!'),
(446, 3, 1, 'Just as I am - and waiting not'),
(446, 3, 2, 'To rid my soul of one dark blot,'),
(446, 3, 3, 'To Thee, whose blood can cleanse each spot,'),
(446, 3, 4, 'O Lamb of God, I come!'),
(446, 4, 1, 'Just as I am - Thy love, I own,'),
(446, 4, 2, 'Has broken every barrier down;'),
(446, 4, 3, 'Now to be Thine, my joy and crown,'),
(446, 4, 4, 'O Lamb of God, I come!'),
(446, 5, 1, 'Just as I am - of that free love'),
(446, 5, 2, 'The fulness and the depth to prove,'),
(446, 5, 3, 'Here for a season, then above -'),
(446, 5, 4, 'O Lamb of God, I come!'),
(447, 1, 1, 'Jesus, of Thee we ne''er would tire;'),
(447, 1, 2, 'The new and living food'),
(447, 1, 3, 'Can satisfy the heart''s desire'),
(447, 1, 4, 'Of those redeemed by blood.'),
(447, 2, 1, 'If such the happy midnight song'),
(447, 2, 2, 'Our prisoned spirits raise,'),
(447, 2, 3, 'What are the joys that cause, ere long,'),
(447, 2, 4, 'Eternal bursts of praise!'),
(447, 3, 1, 'To look within and see no stain,'),
(447, 3, 2, 'Abroad no curse to trace;'),
(447, 3, 3, 'To shed no tears, to feel no pain,'),
(447, 3, 4, 'But see Thee face to face;'),
(447, 4, 1, 'To find each hope of glory gained,'),
(447, 4, 2, 'Fulfilled each precious word;'),
(447, 4, 3, 'And fully all to have attained'),
(447, 4, 4, 'The image of our Lord.'),
(447, 5, 1, 'O may Thy Spirit help us still,'),
(447, 5, 2, 'In this bright hope, to be'),
(447, 5, 3, 'More subject to the Father''s will,'),
(447, 5, 4, 'E''en now much more like Thee.'),
(448, 1, 1, 'Sing aloud to God, our strength!'),
(448, 1, 2, 'He has brought us hitherto;'),
(448, 1, 3, 'He will bring us home at length,'),
(448, 1, 4, 'This the Lord our God will do.'),
(448, 1, 5, 'Doubt not, for His word is stable;'),
(448, 1, 6, 'Fear not, for His arm is able.'),
(448, 2, 1, 'Sing aloud to God, our strength!'),
(448, 2, 2, 'Sing with wonder of His love;'),
(448, 2, 3, 'Who can tell its breadth and length,'),
(448, 2, 4, 'Who below, or who above?'),
(448, 2, 5, 'Who its depth and height can measure?'),
(448, 2, 6, '''Tis a rich unbounded treasure.'),
(448, 3, 1, 'Sing aloud to God, our strength!'),
(448, 3, 2, 'He is with us where we go;'),
(448, 3, 3, 'Fear we not the journey''s length,'),
(448, 3, 4, 'Fear we not the mighty foe;'),
(448, 3, 5, 'All our foes shall be defeated,'),
(448, 3, 6, 'All our journey safe completed.'),
(449, 1, 1, 'Glory to God! we sing:'),
(449, 1, 2, 'Let all their tribute bring'),
(449, 1, 3, 'With one accord!'),
(449, 1, 4, 'His only Son He gave'),
(449, 1, 5, 'The lost to seek and save,'),
(449, 1, 6, 'And raised Him from the grave,'),
(449, 1, 7, 'Jesus, our Lord.'),
(449, 2, 1, 'Glory to God! we sing:'),
(449, 2, 2, 'Let saints with heaven ring'),
(449, 2, 3, 'His praise abroad!'),
(449, 2, 4, 'Jesus, who once did die'),
(449, 2, 5, 'To God to bring us nigh,'),
(449, 2, 6, 'Is crowned as Man on high,'),
(449, 2, 7, 'His God our God.'),
(449, 3, 1, 'Glory to God! we cry:'),
(449, 3, 2, 'Our tongues would magnify'),
(449, 3, 3, 'Jesus our Lord.'),
(449, 3, 4, 'O God, what grace is Thine,'),
(449, 3, 5, 'Revealed in love divine'),
(449, 3, 6, 'By Him! Our hearts enshrine'),
(449, 3, 7, 'Our glorious Lord.'),
(450, 1, 1, 'Blest be the God and Father'),
(450, 1, 2, 'Of Jesus Christ the Son,'),
(450, 1, 3, 'Who chose us for all blessing'),
(450, 1, 4, 'Ere time had yet begun;'),
(450, 1, 5, 'That we, redeemed, His loved ones,'),
(450, 1, 6, 'Might dwell with Him above,'),
(450, 1, 7, 'And know the depth and fulness'),
(450, 1, 8, 'Of His unbounded love.'),
(450, 2, 1, 'Where all those deep affections,'),
(450, 2, 2, 'Which fill the Father''s heart,'),
(450, 2, 3, 'Shall find their satisfaction,'),
(450, 2, 4, 'Their joy to us impart;'),
(450, 2, 5, 'There we, Himself surrounding,'),
(450, 2, 6, 'Shall "Abba Father!" say,'),
(450, 2, 7, 'Within those many mansions,'),
(450, 2, 8, 'Prepared for that day.'),
(450, 3, 1, 'E''en whilst we here are waiting'),
(450, 3, 2, 'His rest on high to share,'),
(450, 3, 3, 'We know our blest relation'),
(450, 3, 4, 'As sons before Him there;'),
(450, 3, 5, 'And by His Spirit''s leading,'),
(450, 3, 6, 'We "Abba, Father!" cry;'),
(450, 3, 7, 'With ever-growing longing'),
(450, 3, 8, 'We seek our place on high.'),
(451, 1, 1, 'Behold the Lamb, with glory crowned!'),
(451, 1, 2, 'To Him all power be giv''n;'),
(451, 1, 3, 'No place too high for Him is found,'),
(451, 1, 4, 'No place too high in heav''n.'),
(451, 2, 1, 'He fills the throne - the throne above;'),
(451, 2, 2, 'Its rights to Him belong;'),
(451, 2, 3, 'The object of His Father''s love,'),
(451, 2, 4, 'Theme of the ransomed''s song.'),
(451, 3, 1, 'Though high, yet He accepts the praise'),
(451, 3, 2, 'His people offer here;'),
(451, 3, 3, 'The faintest, feeblest note they raise'),
(451, 3, 4, 'Will reach the Saviour''s ear.'),
(451, 4, 1, 'This song be ours, we join in one'),
(451, 4, 2, 'To celebrate the Name'),
(451, 4, 3, 'Of Him that sits upon the throne,'),
(451, 4, 4, 'And to exalt the Lamb.'),
(451, 5, 1, 'To Him whom men despise and slight,'),
(451, 5, 2, 'To Him be glory giv''n:'),
(451, 5, 3, 'The crown is His, and His by right'),
(451, 5, 4, 'The highest place in heav''n.'),
(452, 1, 1, 'Lord, to be in Thine own presence'),
(452, 1, 2, 'Joy unspeakable will be;'),
(452, 1, 3, 'We shall there with hearts exulting'),
(452, 1, 4, 'Offer endless praise to Thee.'),
(452, 2, 1, 'Every eye shall then behold Thee,'),
(452, 2, 2, 'Gaze upon Thee as Thou art;'),
(452, 2, 3, 'Every heart, in love delighting,'),
(452, 2, 4, 'Shall fulfil its glorious part.'),
(452, 3, 1, 'Every ear Thine accents hearing,'),
(452, 3, 2, 'Which have quickened us below;'),
(452, 3, 3, 'Every mouth Thy glory telling,'),
(452, 3, 4, 'Filled by Thee, Thy praise to show.'),
(452, 4, 1, 'Blessed Saviour, what rejoicing,'),
(452, 4, 2, 'What delight we then shall share!'),
(452, 4, 3, 'Freed at last to serve unhindered,'),
(452, 4, 4, 'Praising Thee for ever there.'),
(452, 5, 1, 'By the Spirit we already'),
(452, 5, 2, 'Taste of love divine below;'),
(452, 5, 3, 'At Thy feet we praise and worship -'),
(452, 5, 4, 'Love ineffable we know.'),
(453, 1, 1, 'Holy Spirit, Helper nigh,'),
(453, 1, 2, 'Sent in love from God on high'),
(453, 1, 3, 'Here to dwell with us below,'),
(453, 1, 4, 'Thou hast come, and Thee we know.'),
(453, 2, 1, 'Thee we praise, uniting power,'),
(453, 2, 2, 'Comforter for every hour;'),
(453, 2, 3, 'Leader into truth we see'),
(453, 2, 4, 'Meet it is to honour Thee.'),
(453, 3, 1, 'Depths of God by Thee revealed'),
(453, 3, 2, 'To His saints whom Thou hast sealed,'),
(453, 3, 3, 'Earnest of eternal bliss -'),
(453, 3, 4, 'Gladly we give thanks for this.'),
(453, 4, 1, 'Thine anointing, too, we know,'),
(453, 4, 2, 'Once the power on Christ below.'),
(453, 4, 3, 'Thus, as filled by Thee in grace,'),
(453, 4, 4, 'We can take for God our place.'),
(454, 1, 1, 'Father, Thy sons adore Thee,'),
(454, 1, 2, 'For Thou our hearts hast won.'),
(454, 1, 3, 'What joy to be before Thee'),
(454, 1, 4, 'Accepted in Thy Son!'),
(454, 2, 1, 'For sonship through Christ Jesus'),
(454, 2, 2, 'By Thee marked out before:'),
(454, 2, 3, 'What grace abounds toward us!'),
(454, 2, 4, 'We worship and adore.'),
(454, 3, 1, 'According to Thy pleasure,'),
(454, 3, 2, 'Before Thee without fear,'),
(454, 3, 3, 'A love which knows no measure'),
(454, 3, 4, 'Doth rest upon us here.'),
(454, 4, 1, 'Thus, Father, now we worship'),
(454, 4, 2, 'And praise adoringly;'),
(454, 4, 3, 'To Thee be honour, glory,'),
(454, 4, 4, 'Now and eternally.'),
(455, 1, 1, 'There is a Name we love to hear,'),
(455, 1, 2, 'We love to sing its worth;'),
(455, 1, 3, 'It sounds like music in our ear,'),
(455, 1, 4, 'The sweetest Name on earth.'),
(455, 2, 1, 'It tells us of a Saviour''s love,'),
(455, 2, 2, 'Who died to set us free;'),
(455, 2, 3, 'It tells us of His precious blood,'),
(455, 2, 4, 'The sinner''s perfect plea.'),
(455, 3, 1, 'Jesus! the Name we love so well,'),
(455, 3, 2, 'The Name we love to hear;'),
(455, 3, 3, 'No saint on earth its worth can tell,'),
(455, 3, 4, 'No heart conceive how dear.'),
(455, 4, 1, 'This Name shall shed its fragrance still'),
(455, 4, 2, 'Along life''s thorny road,'),
(455, 4, 3, 'Shall sweetly smooth the rugged hill'),
(455, 4, 4, 'That leads us up to God.'),
(455, 5, 1, 'And there the whole triumphant throng'),
(455, 5, 2, 'Of blood-bought saints on high'),
(455, 5, 3, 'Shall sing the new eternal song,'),
(455, 5, 4, 'With Jesus ever nigh.'),
(456, 1, 1, 'Our God we bless Thee for Thy love'),
(456, 1, 2, 'Made manifest in Jesus;'),
(456, 1, 3, 'We praise Thy Name, that by His death'),
(456, 1, 4, 'Thy love from bondage frees us.'),
(456, 2, 1, 'The darkness and the distance gone,'),
(456, 2, 2, 'No longer room for sadness;'),
(456, 2, 3, 'Love''s disposition now made known,'),
(456, 2, 4, 'Thy saints are filled with gladness.'),
(456, 3, 1, 'Thine attributes, O God, are seen'),
(456, 3, 2, 'In Jesus crowned with glory,'),
(456, 3, 3, 'And in our hearts Thy praises ring'),
(456, 3, 4, 'As with Him now before Thee.'),
(456, 4, 1, 'A people formed to show Thy praise,'),
(456, 4, 2, 'From every tongue and nation,'),
(456, 4, 3, 'Rest, in the nearness of Thy love,'),
(456, 4, 4, 'In covenant relation.'),
(456, 5, 1, 'Thy willing people, formed in love'),
(456, 5, 2, 'From which no power shall sever,'),
(456, 5, 3, 'With great delight, with holy hands,'),
(456, 5, 4, 'We''d serve Thee thus for ever.');
INSERT INTO `hymn_line_de` (`hymn_no`, `vers_no`, `line_no`, `line_text`) VALUES (1, 1, 1, 'VON all den Gaben Deiner Lieb -'),
(1, 1, 2, 'Du gibst uns nur, was gut -'),
(1, 1, 3, 'Der Himmel selbst nichts Reichres kennt'),
(1, 1, 4, 'Als des Erl?sers Blut.'),
(1, 2, 1, 'Den Glauben schenkt die Liebe auch,'),
(1, 2, 2, 'Der auf das Blut vertraut,'),
(1, 2, 3, 'Sonst war die Gabe ganz umsonst,'),
(1, 2, 4, 'Obgleich sie einzig traut.'),
(1, 3, 1, 'Wir preisen Dich mit Herz und Sinn,'),
(1, 3, 2, 'Verdanken alles Dir,'),
(1, 3, 3, 'Den Heiland und die Kraft, die Ihn'),
(1, 3, 4, 'Macht kostbar f?r und f?r.'),
(2, 1, 1, 'VATER, Deine Liebe kannte'),
(2, 1, 2, 'Uns schon, eh die Erde war,'),
(2, 1, 3, 'Die uns auch zu Jesu wandte,'),
(2, 1, 4, 'Die so m?chtig, wunderbar,'),
(2, 1, 5, 'Und zu S?hnen'),
(2, 1, 6, 'Machte sie uns immerdar.'),
(2, 2, 1, 'Diese Liebe uns einh?llet,'),
(2, 2, 2, 'All ihr Reichtum kommt uns zu.'),
(2, 2, 3, 'Ihre Kraft uns ganz erf?llet,'),
(2, 2, 4, 'H?lt uns so in heilger Ruh.'),
(2, 2, 5, 'Gott und Vater,'),
(2, 2, 6, 'Dir flie?t die Anbetung zu.'),
(3, 1, 1, 'ALS HAUPT, o Gott, erhaben Du,'),
(3, 1, 2, 'Reichtum und Herrlichkeit sind Dein,'),
(3, 1, 3, 'In Liebe herrschst Du immerzu,'),
(3, 1, 4, 'Als S?hne sind wir darin frei.'),
(3, 2, 1, 'Macht und Gewalt sind Dein allein,'),
(3, 2, 2, 'Und alles f?llt mit Kraft Dein Geist;'),
(3, 2, 3, 'So stimmen wir gest?rkt nun ein'),
(3, 2, 4, 'Ins Lied, das Deinen Namen preist.'),
(3, 3, 1, 'Dein Name herrlich! Unser Geist'),
(3, 3, 2, 'Wird still vom Hauch der Ewigkeit.'),
(3, 3, 3, 'Gott - Vater, Sohn und Heilger Geist -'),
(3, 3, 4, 'Anbetung sei Dir nun geweiht.'),
(4, 1, 1, 'HERR, Deine Liebe uns innig verbindet'),
(4, 1, 2, 'Und aus der W?ste zu Dir uns erhebt,'),
(4, 1, 3, 'Bald wird verherrlicht im Lobe verk?ndet,'),
(4, 1, 4, 'Was schon im Geiste das Herz so belebt.'),
(4, 2, 1, 'W?hrend wir, Herr, auf die Stunde gewartet,'),
(4, 2, 2, 'Hat oft der Tr?ster geredet von Dir.'),
(4, 2, 3, 'Wir sind erf?llt von den Sch?tzen der Liebe,'),
(4, 2, 4, 'Dir, dem Erhabnen, str?mt Wohlduft herf?r.'),
(4, 3, 1, 'F?r uns, Herr Jesu, hast Du Dich gegeben -'),
(4, 3, 2, 'Welch unergr?ndliches Leiden war Dein!'),
(4, 3, 3, 'Du bist vom Preise des Himmels umgeben,'),
(4, 3, 4, 'Dir gilt der Sang unsrer Herzen allein.'),
(4, 4, 1, 'Dich, o Herr Jesu, wir lieben, verehren,'),
(4, 4, 2, 'Ein hocherhabener Name ist Dein!'),
(4, 4, 3, 'Sch?ner als alle bist Du! Wir begehren,'),
(4, 4, 4, 'Dir nun die Antwort der Herzen zu weihn.'),
(5, 1, 1, 'VATER der Herrlichkeit, Dir nun erschallt,'),
(5, 1, 2, 'Da wolkenlos des Himmels Licht uns strahlt,'),
(5, 1, 3, 'Der Lobgesang.'),
(5, 1, 4, 'Ruhm eines Plans vergangner Ewigkeit,'),
(5, 1, 5, 'Unwandelbarer Liebe Herrlichkeit'),
(5, 1, 6, 'Sind Dein fortan.'),
(5, 2, 1, 'Wie herrlich ist''s, Du warst vor aller Zeit,'),
(5, 2, 2, 'Vor dem Gesch?pf, das jetzt durch Gnade teilt'),
(5, 2, 3, 'Dein Liebesherz.'),
(5, 2, 4, 'Wir beten an, erhaben ist Dein Plan:'),
(5, 2, 5, 'Als S?hne sind wir mit dem Sohn fortan'),
(5, 2, 6, 'Nah Deinem Herz.'),
(5, 3, 1, 'Dein Herz zu stillen, solches ward erdacht,'),
(5, 3, 2, 'Sein war der Leidenspfad, bis es vollbracht,'),
(5, 3, 3, 'Das Werk getan!'),
(5, 3, 4, 'Ohn unser Zutun ward uns dieses Los,'),
(5, 3, 5, 'Als die gezogen in der Liebe Scho?,'),
(5, 3, 6, 'Zu beten an!'),
(5, 4, 1, 'Wir beten, Vater, an, erkennen schon,'),
(5, 4, 2, 'Da? Du nun reicher durch der Liebe Lohn'),
(5, 4, 3, 'Wie Du''s begehrt.'),
(5, 4, 4, 'Zu Deinem Reichtum kommt auf immerdar,'),
(5, 4, 5, 'Dein Haus zu f?llen, eine Menschenschar,'),
(5, 4, 6, 'Die Dich verehrt.'),
(6, 1, 1, 'WAS macht Dein Name Jesus kund'),
(6, 1, 2, 'F?r jedes offne Ohr!'),
(6, 1, 3, 'Der S?nder, dem vergeben ist,'),
(6, 1, 4, 'Liebt Ihn, wie nichts zuvor.'),
(6, 2, 1, 'Dein Name k?ndet jede Gnad,'),
(6, 2, 2, 'Die Gott als Mensch erweist;'),
(6, 2, 3, 'Ein g?ttlich Leben ward gesehn'),
(6, 2, 4, 'In Ihm, den Gnade preist.'),
(6, 3, 1, 'Er spricht vom Leben voller Lieb,'),
(6, 3, 2, 'In Sanftmut, Leid ge?bt,'),
(6, 3, 3, 'Er zeugt von Seinem Mitgef?hl,'),
(6, 3, 4, 'Was immer uns betr?bt.'),
(6, 4, 1, 'Du S?ndenloser wardst f?r uns'),
(6, 4, 2, 'Zur S?nde dort gemacht,'),
(6, 4, 3, 'Das Herz gewinnen wolltest Du'),
(6, 4, 4, 'Und hast Dich dargebracht.'),
(6, 5, 1, 'Dein Name neigt das Herz Dir zu,'),
(6, 5, 2, 'Macht es zum Lob bereit.'),
(6, 5, 3, 'Du bist der Sch?nste allzumal,'),
(6, 5, 4, 'Des Liebe uns befreit.'),
(7, 1, 1, 'IHR HEILGEN, horcht, erhebt die Stimm'),
(7, 1, 2, 'Und sagt der Welt, wie wir uns freun -'),
(7, 1, 3, 'Der Himmel unser Heim.'),
(7, 1, 4, 'Dort unser Haupt gekr?nt mit Ehr;'),
(7, 1, 5, 'Sein Reich erwartend, rufen wir'),
(7, 1, 6, 'Nun all: Herr Jesu, komm!'),
(8, 1, 1, 'O GOTT, Deine Gr??e'),
(8, 1, 2, 'Und Pracht wir erkennen,'),
(8, 1, 3, 'Im Himmel, auf Erden'),
(8, 1, 4, 'Ist alles von Dir.'),
(8, 1, 5, 'Wie gro? Deine F?lle!'),
(8, 1, 6, 'Erhaben und pr?chtig'),
(8, 1, 7, 'Bist Du, Amen, Amen,'),
(8, 1, 8, 'Anbetung sei Dir!'),
(9, 1, 1, 'ERHEBT des Namens Jesu Macht,'),
(9, 1, 2, 'Beugt euch und gebt Ihm Ehr!'),
(9, 1, 3, 'Vereint wird Ihm das Lob gebracht'),
(9, 1, 4, 'Und kr?nt Ihn, aller Herr!'),
(9, 2, 1, 'Ihr, die erl?st von Adams Art,'),
(9, 2, 2, 'Vom Fall erkauft - wie hehr! -'),
(9, 2, 3, 'R?hmt Ihn, der rettet voller Gnad,'),
(9, 2, 4, 'Und kr?nt Ihn, aller Herr!'),
(9, 3, 1, 'Ruft aus den Namen, der allein'),
(9, 3, 2, 'Zum Heil dient immer mehr;'),
(9, 3, 3, 'Verehrt m?g Er von Scharen sein'),
(9, 3, 4, 'Und kr?nt Ihn, aller Herr!'),
(9, 4, 1, 'Dort beugt sich die erl?ste Schar,'),
(9, 4, 2, 'Ob Seiner Liebe Meer.'),
(9, 4, 3, 'Ja, stimmet ein auf immerdar'),
(9, 4, 4, 'Und kr?nt Ihn, aller Herr!'),
(10, 1, 1, 'O UNSER Gott und Vater, m?gen wir'),
(10, 1, 2, 'Ruhn im Bewu?tsein Deiner Liebe hier,'),
(10, 1, 3, 'Bewahrt in Ihm, der starb und auferstand,'),
(10, 1, 4, 'Bis wir vereint in Deiner Ruhe Land!'),
(11, 1, 1, 'DU bist das fleischgewordne Wort,'),
(11, 1, 2, 'Des Vaters einger Sohn,'),
(11, 1, 3, 'Gott offenbart, gesehn, geh?rt,'),
(11, 1, 4, 'Des Himmels Freud und Wonn:'),
(11, 1, 5, 'Dir, Gottes Lamm, erh?hter Herr,'),
(11, 1, 6, 'Geb?hrt auf ewig Ruhm und Ehr!'),
(11, 2, 1, 'In Dir ward in Vollkommenheit'),
(11, 2, 2, 'Der Vater offenbar,'),
